reviews.text: Rothenburg is definitely worth visiting. Very charming. I would even stay one full night if I came again.
reviews.title: Rothenburg is charming

reviews.text: Lovely trip all around, really enjoyed Harburg castle, our tour lady was so personable and Rothenburg was such an amazing place to explore, could have spent longer in this town. The time was enough, would love to come back to this region in the future. Really enjoyable trip.
reviews.title: Excellent day out.

reviews.text:
Our trip was canceled due to weather.  I understand, if the bus driver does not want to be on the road, I don't either.  We arrived at the noted time and place to begin our tour and were notified at that time (no email or notice before) that the tour was canceled due to weather.  Totally understand.  We were offered a refund or another tour.  Due to our schedule, we chose the refund.  We emailed, as directed, requesting a refund.  We heard nothing.  We have emailed 2 additional times requesting a refund and again, have heard nothing.  No response, no refund.  
Beware!!!
reviews.title: No refund when they cancel the trip

reviews.text: The most amazing trip, Rothenburg is so perfectly preserved it didn’t seem real! Like walking around in a fairytale; the tour exceeded my expectation and the tour guide Jackie was so knowledgeable and very entertaining!  This tour is a MUST
reviews.title: Picture Perfect.

reviews.text: You got there and was able to do what you wanted. Pick up and drop off was easy just need to get there earlier than recommended
reviews.title: You got there and was...

reviews.text: Harburg castle was ok and informative.  Not much to do other than visit the castle. On the other hand, Rothenburg was amazing!  This medieval town/village and the Christmas markets were outstanding!  It’s picturesque, quaint, and full of restaurant, cafes and shops. We only had 3 hrs and would’ve rather skipped Harburg and spent the entire trip here.  Our next visit to Germany, we’ll plan a few extra days and stay in this beautiful village.
reviews.title: Rothenburg is a MUST SEE!

reviews.text: What a great day trip! The transportation was easy to find via Google maps. The tour at Harburg was a delight. Our bus was split into two groups which was nice as we could hear our tour guide well. Our time in Rothenburg was so much fun. It was really just a matter of “how much can I cram into 3 hours?!” We walked through the Christmas markets and got lunch on the go, did a tour at St Jakobs Lutheran Church, and took our time shopping on on the walk back to the bus. We even stopped to get some schneeballen which were recommended by our tour guide (and now I recommend them to you!!)
reviews.title: Wonderful Day Trip!!

reviews.text:
The places that we visit were nice. The castle tour was ok. Bus was really comfortable but we can’t hear anything of the audio so we miss some info about our tour.
Rothenburg was really nice but I felt that we need a little “walking tour” to see the points of interest and not just going by our own.
reviews.title: Tour was ok but I was expecting more

reviews.text: Everyone I met was in a jovial mood and very excited to celebrate Christmas and each other.  I’ve never been in a more festive atmosphere.
reviews.title: That Christmas Atmosphere

reviews.text: Rothenberg is a long way from Munich. It took 3.5 hours to return as no stop off. I think that is something to bare in mind. Rothenberg is stunning we loved the medieval architecture, beautifully decorated for Chrsitmas, pleased we went. The castle on route and castle guide were also really interesting and enthusiastic. It's a shame this trip can't be done on the train independently, it was going to be too long with a lot of changes. Our guide Babara I would say came across rather flat, which on a long trip is a shame. She also recommended at resturant with not great reviews, she seemed keen we all eat there telling us there were limited options, I felt there maybe a commision system there. I would also make sure you get on the right bus and be very clear, before departure Lots of trip buses leave from the same spot. One couple ended up on the wrong trip as tickets weren't checked properly.  4 stars for the location. The actual tour  company would be a low 3.
reviews.title: Rothenberg Beautiful. Tour company mediocre

reviews.text: Harburg Castle depicts medieval living and it is awesome. Whereas, Rothenburg Village is beautiful. The christmas markets were fun. Our experience was a once in a lifetime getaway and it was amazing. We’ve enjoyed this trip.
reviews.title: Unforgettable Experience

reviews.text: The organisation of the trip cannot be faulted. Everything went to the advertised time. Given the distances involved it was inevitably a long day, nearly eleven hours but, that again, was pre-warned. The half-way stop at Harburg Castle with the opportunity for a guided tour (addition 10 Euros pp) was well worth it. A real medieval castle with a long history of being the target of many sieges. Then onward to Rothenburg when, sadly, things began to deteriorate. Not, I hasten to add, any fault of Viator or the tour operator. A Saturday before Christmas was probably the wrong time to visit. To say the town was rammed would be an understatement. Rothenburg might be the most attractive town in Germany but not when one is jostled from crowded coach park to market square and back!
reviews.title: Good organisation but poor choice of date!

reviews.text:
Spent too long at Harburg Castle; well over 1hr as we were split into 2 groups, and had to wait for others to start. For people who weren't doing the castle tour, there was nothing much to do. Would have been better if a) we stopped at the village and/or b) tour was cut down in length.

Rothenburg was nice, and could have spent longer.

3hr bus journey back was far too long.
reviews.title: Interesting, but very long day

reviews.text: Our tour guide was Monika. Very nice, helpful lady who told us history and legends. The bus was extremely comfortable and the driver mades us feel safe.
reviews.title: Nice tour, lovely town

reviews.text: Monica was wonderful and our driver. Enjoyed the castle tour. Wished the Rothenburg time was longer. There is so much to see with so little time

reviews.text:
The tour was pretty good, we got to see Linderhof and Neuschwanstein with plenty of time and local guides from the castles guided us. Even though we were under heavy snow, we departed and arrived safely and on time. We didn’t get much time in Obergammergau however. 
The one complaint that everyone in the tour had was the company’s on-bus “guide.” He spoke broken English, had a thick, unintelligible accent, and made really long pauses within sentences that just were annoying. His information was also straight out from Wikipedia.
Overall a good tour, but the “guide” could use some training.
reviews.title: Almost perfect, great itinerary, on-bus “guide” was annoying

reviews.text: Great tour. We enjoyed our guide Ursula immensely. Very informative.  Beautiful castles. I would recommend as a day trip from munich.

reviews.text: The castles and Oberammagau was amazing. The tour guide was hopeless - barely spoke English (even though this was the English speaking tour), was giving a very painful and disjointed commentary and was clearly reading scant information from his phone. You guys need to have better tour guides
reviews.title: Sights were amazing - need a better tour guide!

reviews.text:
Be prepared to walk a lot. Or to pay money for shuttles at Neuschwanstein, but honestly, the hike is worth it. All in all, it was a good trip and wonderful to see the countryside outside of the city. The palace is pretty cool, but small. Neuschwanstein is impressive, but it's hard not to feel like it's an extremely elaborate set at an amusement park. The tour of the castle is about the same length as the palace since only about 30% of the castle is finished. That was somewhat disappointing, given the $33 price tag for admission to both buildings. 

The Viator tour guide didn't really do much. He was nice and provided a few interesting facts at a few parts during the long driving sections, but he pretty much left us to our own devices once we were parked and our tickets were dispersed at the castle. It was a very expensive day for what boiled down to mostly chaperoned transportation.
reviews.title: Long, expensive day, but mostly worth it

reviews.text: As dreamy as expected! Everything was beautiful. Online searches showed that tours were sold out, but when we got to the ticket counter they were available. Tour lasted an hour, which was plenty long enough.

reviews.text: A perfect day exploring these beautiful places! Each one was an absolute delight. Highly recommended tour. Ahmed, our guide, was super helpful. Bus ride was very comfortable. We were very lucky - blue skies and great weather for December. The only thing which was unfortunate were guests who could not be on time - while everyone else sat and waited on the bus for them. Not sure what can be done about this - really felt for Ahmed who was trying to keep everyone happy.

reviews.text:
I booked a city and desert tour combo and really was glad I booked both! I was travelling solo and booked the tour for myself only and was abit nervous going on the private trip by myself (as it was my first time travelling solo like this). But my tour guide, Ismail, was the most considerate and respectful guide and made me comfortable. 
We did the city tour in the early morning, which was  all very interesting because Ismail would give you extra information about Qatar beyond what you see to understand the culture and living in Qatar. I did feel the city tour was worth it if you enjoy the more laid back touring and observing scenery type of vibe. Apparently the city tour is better later in the afternoon/evening when it is busier to really see the life of Qataris and to experience it. But nevertheless, it was worth the experience. 
I was beyond glad that the combo tour included the desert tour which was probably the best part of the tour! It is exhilarating! You will experience camel ride (which will cost 20 QR for a short experience which is mostly what you need for photos, you can pay more for longer rides), beautiful desert scenery, dune bashing (which Ismail was extremely experienced at with his driving skills), sand boarding and seeing the borders/mountains of Saudi Arabia from Qatar which you can end off with a beautiful swim (and the water feels amazing). 
I would recommend the combo tour to anyone! But if you are only seeking some adrenaline rush, then the desert tour is it! If you are travelling alone like me, you will still be looked after by your tour guide as he will make sure you are enjoying yourself and bring the car closer to you if your feet are burning from the desert sand. Thank you Ismail for the wonderful experience and being such a great tour guide.
reviews.title: You will not regret it …

We loved our tour with Ismael!! Since the moment he picked us up at the hotel until he kindly dropped us off at the airport he made sure that we were doing what we wanted, we had all the information about Doha/Qatar as he could could provide and made sure we had FUN!!! He is polite, educated and funny, and one hell of a great desert driver!  The sand blasting is just so much fun people should enjoy it and let him do it, even though it may seem scary.  He knows what he is doing and it’s a one in a life time experience!! He is also a great photographer and too gorgeous photos of me and my friend!  
Don’t hesitate to pay for any tour because they are worth it. And make sure to ask for Ismael. He will do his best to make your experience unforgettable! I can’t wait to go back to Doha/Qatar and explore other parts of the country!

reviews.text: I decided to avail of a transit visit to Doha on my way back to the United States. This tour caught my attention as it covered what otherwise would have been two separate tours. I only had one full day so this was just perfect for me. My tour guide was Ismael who was very nice, kind and capable. He brought me to the different must-see spots in Doha, that included the Katara Cultural Village, the Pearl Island, the Souq Waqif and the National Museum of Qatar. He provided important information about these places. After the city tour we drove south to visit the sand dunes where I rode a camel and experienced dune bashing for the first time. Dune bashing was thrilling and exciting and I am glad I did it with Ismael who was a talented and safe driver , with lots of experience driving on the dunes. I hope to visit Doha again when the weather is milder, and have more time to explore the city.
reviews.title: Prefect for a transit visit

reviews.text: Kochi Backwater Day Cruise , this is a must if UR visiting with a stay in Kochi . The boat jetty is just past the Lakeshore Hospital at the end of the road . U have to book it at least 2 days ahead . Mr Panicker is a very pleasant gentleman very keen to please U. Raji the boat driver / guide was also happy to please U. The  motor boat is a 8 seater with shaded areas , They provide U with  life jackets and provide a printed  instruction card as to how to wear it and what to do in case of an emergency . There is a fire extinguisher on board as well . The chairs have cushions and very comfortable . Because of slow tourist visits due to Covid their business has been scaled down . They use to provide a onboard kitchen for lunch this was also summer time so that was not offered , bottled water is available and there is a clean toilet at the jetty but not on board . The tour price person or group is quite reasonable, for the 3 hour tour . They stop on different islands in the back waters , at fisherman’s homes and , fishery farms . If U want to buy fresh fish , make sure U bring plastic bags . Wear a hat and make sure U have Sun screen . There is a nice breeze when the boat is moving , but being April it can be hot . We bought some fresh River fish and clams from the fisherman . Different migratory birds in plenty are seen in December to February. We saw some Siberian Cranes who come to feed on the clams . Best to bring glasses for bird watching . The mangroves are beautiful to see . Fisherman ‘s homes are simple & practical . They have to use a boat to come to the mainland . They have electricity and running clean tap water . The fisherman R very friendly . Bring UR camera . Yes I would definitely do this again on my next visit to Kochi , hopefully in winter for bird watching .
reviews.title: Beautiful Kochi Backwaters Experience

reviews.text:
I was met at my hotel by Sando, my English speaking guide for the day.  Our driver, Mejo was stuck in traffic, so we took a tuk tuk to meet the driver in order to stay on schedule.  At the dock, we completed the paperwork then took a water taxi to the beautiful houseboat.  I was traveling solo but felt very comfortable all throughout the day, chatting with Sando. On board the 3 crew introduced themselves and made me feel at home.  The cruise is beautiful through the backwaters, passing homes where life on the water is seen first hand - fishing, swimming, washing clothes, bathing and fields of rice during harvest season.  Saw many species of birds.  Some of the travel is on the open water out in the bay also.  Lunch was delicious and so much food.  There were many choices, all very delicious.  The cook even offered to show us how to make one of the tomato dishes that was great and something even I could make at home.  Yes, I even got a private cooking lesson in the galley.  So enjoyable, the day went by so very quickly.
Yes, it's expensive for one person, and with the added expense for an English speaking guide, but it's a once in a lifetime experience that should not be passed up.  I loved every minute of it.  That evening when I was dropped off at my hotel I felt that the day could have not been more perfect.
reviews.title: Pleasant Day Cruise

reviews.text: My wife and I had a great time touring the city with our guide, Yogesh (Yogi). He gave thoughtful historical context about the architecture, city layout and historical figures significant to the history of India and Jodhpur specifically. There is no question that the man knows his city well. We were able to venture to incredible vantage points for memorable views of the city. The tour definitely takes you through roads less traveled by and Yogesh did a great job safely navigating us through the narrow alleys and chaos that could prove challenging to unaided tourists. Lastly we were able to sample some delicious chai and samosas through local vendors. Yogesh is proficient in several languages and has has worked with many foreign tourists. I would highly recommend him for the average tourist, but also to any Indians born abroad that would like to get a better sense of their history. I could not recommend this tour without the highest enthusiasm.
reviews.title: Amazing guide a worthwhile experience

If you’re in Jodhpur this is a great way to experience the Blue City. Deepak was friendly, spoke immaculate English and he seemed to enjoy answering our questions as we walked through the backstreets that we wouldn’t have found on our own.

A visit to a textile shop or similar is pretty common in tours here but for us, we could have done without it. Deepak did ask us if we wanted to go and was honest about the commission he earns if we buy something so this isn’t a criticism of him or his tour, just mentioning it in case you want to avoid awkwardly needing to look around a shop of things you’re not going to buy.

reviews.text:
I just want to take the time to write this review and say how incredible not only the city tour was, but how kind and genuine Deepak is. 
We booked a city tour for 9am, however, the morning of the tour my wife wasn't feeling too good. So I went to reception and spoke to Deepak about delaying for an hour or so, to see if there were any improvements. Deepak was more than happy to delay the tour to wait for my wife, even as far as me coming down to reception again at 11am to say my wife wasn't any better and Deepak saying, that's totally fine, 'we are not doing the tour without her, I want to show both of you my city'. So he suggested waiting until 4pm, whilst also giving suggestions on things that would help my wife feel better. Come 4pm, my wife was feeling a lot better and we went on the city tour.  We both had a great experience, loved visiting the Fort, wandering the streets of the 'blue city' and then ended in a stunning 450 year old building enjoying a beer on a roof top terrace, with an outstanding view of the hilltop fort. It was a great afternoon. And thanks to Deepaks patience and kindness, we both got to enjoy the tour and the city. 
Would highly recommend.
reviews.title: Jodhpur City Tour with an Amazing Guide

reviews.text: This was easily the most authentic and genuine walking tour I have ever taken.  Soham takes you through Kolkata’s old city in the manner only a local can.  He is friendly, kind, and knowledgeable.  He loves Kolkata and you will not regret it. Fully recommended 10/10. Thanks Soham!
reviews.title: Kolkata - no filter!

reviews.text: Soham was our Guide and showed us a unique city at a unique time. Experiencing the start of a normal day in Kolkata and utilizing the many various types of public transportation was a fun and exciting way to see the different parts. Soham was very knowledgeable and I surely learnt a lot from his explanations and answers to our questions. We also were able to have the tasting senses energized with delicious Karak and a traditional local breakfast that even the Locals were lining up and waiting for a table for. This tour has been well thought out to cover and tick so many boxes. It’s 100% definitely worth getting up at 6am and the photos shared after the tour is also a very nice touch. Thoroughly enjoyed the tour and would be very honored to recommend Soham as a fabulous Ambassador and Guide of his City and Country to all of my friends and family. I will stay in touch with Soham as I’m sure I will visit this special City again in the near future.
reviews.title: The Smiling Soham.

reviews.text: It was a great your, Sohan is very knowledgeable and knows how to navigate the city and narrate stories. Really enjoyed the morning walk!
reviews.title: Great walk to kick off the day!

reviews.text: An amazing experience, the best way to feel like a local. Soham went above and beyond, and the trip ending up being longer than expected (in a good way). The breakfast spot was amazing, and cramming in so many different modes of transport was something I wouldn’t have done on my own.
reviews.title: Perfect

reviews.text: Joined the morning tour that started at 6am, fortunately weren’t staying too far from the meeting point. Didn’t know what to expect but from the start found our tour guide Soham to be very friendly, the tour lasted 4.5 hours and encompassed  a faste of Calcutta life. What came across is that Soham has a genuine passion for guiding and enabling visitors to taste and glimpse Calcutta. Personally I find his talks and explanations struck a good balance between being too long or over detailed and giving us enough to understand the part of Calcutta we were in. Cannot recommend Soham enough, have one more day in Calcutta and already booked another tour with him before I head back home to explore Diwali.
reviews.title: My Calcutta experience

reviews.text: One of the best walking tours that I have done. My wife and I went in the third week of September. It was only us so it became a private tour. Soham, was excellent! Taking us through different landmarks in kolkata while weaving beautiful stories. I grew up in kolkata and left when I was young and still found this to have tremendous value in terms of knowledge and entertainment. Soham went above and beyond to make this special for is. I highly recommend his walking tours!
reviews.title: Amazing! Highly Recommended!

reviews.text:
This is a perfectly curated tour for someone who wants to experience the local culture, know about the history of the city and get introduced the Bengali way of life.  I was travelling solo and had a day in kolkata and wanted to experience the real Bengali way....Needless to day this tour checked off all my boxes!
We took a walk through the city starting early in the morning,  used all of the local transport, walked over the howrah bridge, ate delicious food and had a nice long chat over Chai!😊 Also, experienced the bustling flower market and heard stories of Durga and Kali in kumartuli!
Soham was very polite, funny and a fantastic story teller! He also made sure to keep me informed about where we were going next and moved at a comfy pace...More importantly I felt very safe...which was important because I was travelling solo. At the end he recommended lots of things I could do with the rest of the day and even helped me plan all that I wanted to do!
I can say that I'm going to take all these stories home and kolkat a made me fall in love with India a bit more today😊
I recommend this 100 percent!
reviews.title: Charming Kolkata morning!

reviews.text: We had a great time! It was an early start but It was cool to watch the city come to life. The monsoon rains didn’t affect the walk. The tour was very interesting and we learned a lot about how the city is organized. The traditional breakfast was a perfect ending. Our guide, Soham, sent us the photos he took during the walk and he is a good photographer. Thanks. I suspect that this tour was the highlight of our brief visit in kolkata!
reviews.title: Highlight of Kolkata visit

reviews.text: We recently went to kolkata and to take a trip with  calcutta capsule was the best decision which we ever made ..Mr Soham was a amazing human and his knowledge about his lovely calcutta is just amazing...Magical hour was our favourite...Never ever miss Calcutta capsule once you are in Calcutta
reviews.title: Don't ever miss this Gem!!!!

reviews.text: This walk around Kolkata following Soham's steps was just exquisite. It's a carefully thought out route, full of touching details, and Soham is such a storyteller that it is hard not to fall in love with the city. An experience not to miss. Thanks Soham :-)
reviews.title: So much more than sightseeing

reviews.text: This was an absolutely amazing tour of Kolkata, it had everything, you really get to immerse yourself into the everyday life of Kolkattan people. You see this vibrant city come to life, full of colour the senses are stimulated in every situation. Soham is an amazing guide, you really know this guy loves his city and is proud to show off everything it has to offer. I would highly recommend this tour. You get to move around the city on nearly every mode of transport it has. The breakfast was amazing. Soham really knows authentic Kolkata and wants to share it with others.
reviews.title: Get the feel for Kolkata from the average person's point of view. Move around the city like you would at home. Amazing.

reviews.text: The tour was an amazing experience.  I'm of Bengali origin and have been coming to Kolkata my whole life.  Soham took me to off the beaten path places and experiences in Kolkata that I've never been before,  In addition, he told me stories about the history, tradition, culture and everyday life in Kolkata in a special and unique way.  This was one of the best tours I've taken and one I'll remember forever.
reviews.title: Amazing Kolkata Tour!

reviews.text: Great experience. Woke up at 5:30 am to begin an exploration of the city. Loved starting early to finish the heat. Would definitely recommend to friends and family visiting Calcutta!

reviews.text: The tour is fantastic. Soham takes you to places that alone you probably won’t find or even know the existence of. Soham knows literally every corner, habit, … etc of Kolkata. The local tea and breakfast were delicious. If you ask me this tour should be mandatory for every foreigner arriving in Kolkata.  You  get many insights that make you understand the people, life and culture of Kolkata. I recommend 200%.
reviews.title: Great insights of non touristic parts of the city

reviews.text: In 4 hrs you get a microcosm of life in Calcutta, a masterful composition of experiences in this city that's teeming with life -- flower market, Ganges rituals, itinerant priests, Meydan, bus/taxi/ferry, Howrah bridge, authentic eatery, streetside tea, architecture, deity-making studios, etc; wonderul blend of life as is echoing the distant past; Soham has put this together with a great deal of thought and creativity; thanks for this unforgettable experience! Younes Jalali
reviews.title: Enthralling!

reviews.text: My first visit to Kolkata proved to be a fabulous surprise and revelation. I connected with Soham in February after following his Calcutta Capsule Instagram account for 12 months and his correspondence and planning were Superb. These Included airport pickup to his Owls Nest Airbnb followed by his Magic Hour Tour and train to Varanasi. The accommodation was excellent with a lovely roof terrace with a plethora of bird life over looking the parks of the Old Town. The Magic Hour Tour included all modes of transport walking, ferries, auto rickshaw, buses, ambassador taxis which were great fun and Soham passionately provided an extremely comprehensive and professional historical, cultural & economic overview throughout the whole City. It far exceeded our expectations and I would highly recommend The Magic Hour Tour with Soham. Many thanks Soham & TC for a visit of a Life Time!
reviews.title: Expert Highly Quality Fun Tour

reviews.text: This is the 3rd tour I have been on with Soham and all have been fantastic. He is so informative and gives so much information. This tour was one of my favourites, we saw so much of Kolkata which you would only be able to with a local. So many hidden places and amazing sights! I would recommend this to anyone visiting Kolkata!
reviews.title: Must do when in Kolkata!

reviews.text:
The Magic Hour Tour by Soham from Calcutta Capsules is my number one recommendation if you're visiting Kolkata and would like to experience it beyond the famous tourist sites. It's so thoughtfully curated to include all the lovely quirks of this city — taking you through the quiet, early-morning neighborhoods to visiting the delightfully busy flower market, and even taking a lovely walk on the Howrah bridge (among many, many other things!) I absolutely loved how we had a chance to travel using all the different public modes of transport and have a traditional Bengali breakfast at the end :) And throughout the tour, Soham was incredibly invested in helping us understand the city's history and culture, along with ensuring we had a hassle-free experience.

Congratulations on putting together this lovely tour! :)
reviews.title: Don't miss it!

reviews.text:
Fantastic company, very trust worthy and professional. The guides where all nice, professional and knowledgeable. Special mention to Ali who truly is a gentleman and B J in Jaipur who made the experience in the city. 
Our driver Satvinder my partner and I cannot speak highly enough off. He was kind, extremely polite, courteous and wonderfully genuine. Throughout our time with him we learnt alot, not only about the places we were visiting but also with local knowledge guidance and advice. A kind sense of humour also was really nice. We would like to say a public and personal thank you to him, he is a credit to the business and we felt our trip wouldn't have been the same without him. 
We would highly recommend the tour business, driver and guides for a safe, reliable and utterly pleasent experience in India.

reviews.text: What a great experience! The distance from each city is quite long so we didn’t know what to expect. Surprisingly, the driver told us so much about Indian culture, religion, good places to see or to eat and even about his family when asked. He was so sweet and nice the whole time. He went above and beyond to make us feel comfortable and welcome. I can’t recommend this company enough. What a trip!
reviews.title: Great driver!

reviews.text: We are a group of four and have just returned from an amazing first visit to India.  We came across this company on Tripadvisor and after reading the reviews decided to book.  We didn't regret it.  Prior to our arrival Sugar was very attentive and responded almost immediately to any questions we had.  We met our driver Sushil on the first day in Delhi and he accompanied us on our tour of Delhi and then took us to Agra and Jaipur.  Each day we had a local guide who took us to all the important sights, Sushil dropped us off at each point of interest and collected us when we were finished.  Our guides, Saurob in Delhi, Rahoul in Agra, Ali in Fatehpur Sikri, and BK in Jaipur were all excellent and had a great knowledge of all the sights we visited.  Sushil was great company on the drives and he educated us on local customs and traditions.  We had great fun with him.   If you are an independent traveller this company provides tremendous service and reassurance and we have been recommending them to our friends.  We will certainly be back!
reviews.title: Amazing Experience

reviews.text:
We are so pleased that we used Discover India By Car as it was the perfect way to do the Golden Triangle. We were given a recommendation by friends who traveled in 2018 and we're not disappointed. Our driver, Sushil was a star who kept his calm despite what to us were crazy road conditions! We felt safe at all times. 
Our guides kept us informed of all we saw and they tailored our program to suit our interests. 
Travelling by car was a great way to experience "Real India" particularly when accompanied by Sushil who had many amusing and informative things to tell us!
We will definitely be recommending this company ( and Driver!) to friends that plan to travel to India in future.
reviews.title: Star in a Car!

reviews.text: Booking with DIBC was the smartest decision we made when booking our trip to India. From the moment we inquired with Sugar, to starting our 5 day trip, to the very end, we were cared for and learned so much about the Indian culture. My wife and I visited from the U.S. and were so impressed with the punctuality, service, and safety given to us by our phenomenal driver, Mr. Parveen, and the great guides we had each day. We did Delhi to Agra, Agra to Jaipur, and Jaipur to Delhi, with a guide in each city. I highly recommend opting for the tour guides as they are all professional and offer priceless insights. Again, I highly recommend our driver Mr. Parveen. He is exceptional. Thank you Mr. Parveen for the unforgettable trip.
reviews.title: 5 Star Experience - Highly Recommend!

reviews.text:
Look no further than Discover India by Car for your specialised tour of India. Ankit (Sugar) listened to all my needs in booking a trip, suggested amazing insights to our itinerary, was prompt with his response, and at a fair price. My wife and I were visiting from the United States and looking for a private tour of the Golden Triangle. Our driver, Parveen, was always on time, a phenomenal driver, offered great insights, and went above and beyond to make our trip remarkable. We were in Jaipur for Diwali weekend, leaving right before the festivities, and he suggested and led with us a special Rick-shaw ride through the streets of Jaipur to admire the atmosphere of gorgeous lights. It was something we will never forget, and will always appreciate his willingness to show us something so special. Our tour guides in each city were also incredible. DIBC does a phenomenal job choosing the guides. All of them have many, many years of experience and insights. One of our favorites was in Jaipur, mr B.K., was so knowledgeable and shared personal stories and experiences into culture at each destination. Even taking us to amazing monuments and temples on the way that we hadn’t planned.
I will be recommending Parveen and DBCI to all that want to travel to India. It is a top company and best experience possible! Thank you Parveen for all you did for us!
reviews.title: Amazing experience- definitely book with DIBC!

reviews.text: Mr. Narender, probably the best driver the company got, came to pick us up at the airport and took us in five days smooth and safely to numerous sights in Agra, Jaipur and Delhi. Mr. Narender was friendly, knew where he needed to drive, was easy talking to, he kept the car clean and above all he slid through traffic like there was no traffic but believe me, there was a lot of traffic !!  If I come back I'll ask for him for sure !!
reviews.title: happy to have made the trip with Mr. Narender as our driver !!

reviews.text:

reviews.title: Wonderful experience for our first India trip

reviews.text:
We had an absolutely amazing week exploring India with Discover India by Car. Prior to our journey, Sugar and the team went above and beyond to ensure we made the most of our entire week.

When we arrived, Satvinder warmly welcomed us and provided us with invaluable insights into the country's rich history, all while maintaining a great sense of humour and remarkable patience, especially when it came to our 7 and 8-year-old children.

Our guides were truly exceptional, knowing precisely when to delve deep into history and when to keep the pace. Notably Ali and BK would be guides that we reccomend you request at specific locations. 

To anyone contemplating this journey, don't hesitate – book it without delay. We, for one, are already planning our return to this incredible country.
reviews.title: A week to remember

reviews.text: This trip was fantastic with Sugar and his team making the organising and planning so simple and easy. Satvindhar was our driver for the week and he was outstanding. He supported our every request and was excellent with our 2 young children. For anyone considering India with their family this is the way to do it. We were supported and cared for and every tour guide Satvindhar made sure was the best he could get and it showed every day at each attraction.
reviews.title: Trip of a life time, exceeding expectations

reviews.text:
We contacted Sugar back in February 2023, looking for a car and driver, so we could visit the Golden Triangle - Delhi, Jaipur & of course Agra and the amazing Taj Mahal. We wanted to be collected from the airport, driven around for 10 days and eventually returned to the airport for our trip home. Sugar suggested an itinerary, which was pretty much exactly what we wanted to cover, but we weren’t under any pressure to follow it exactly and could add anywhere that we wanted to visit. I thought that the price was extremely good and no payment was required until the end of the trip, so there was no financial risk.
We arrived at Delhi airport to be met by Sushil, our driver for the next ten days. He was amazing …. bearing in mind he is not a guide (Sugar organised an official guide for certain places) he was very knowledgeable and his English is excellent. We chose the hotels we wanted to stay at and booked those online independently, some meals we ate at the hotels but, when requested, Sushil made some excellent suggestions and drove us there in the evening and collected us when we had finished. No Delhi Belly for the whole trip!
All in all Sushil made our visit to India unforgettable and I’d highly recommend this company.
reviews.title: Amazing Golden Triangle Trip

reviews.text: I had the best time travelling around the Golden Triangle. Communication from the beginning was very prompt and detailed. My driver Mr Parveen was very kind and courteous throughout the tour. Nothing was too much and he was happy to offer suggestions on timings and places to see. Leaving Delhi, I asked if I could see some street art and this was no problem for Mr Praveen. He brought me down different streets and gave me lots of time to take pictures.  The car was spotlessly clean every day with charging ports in the back and wifi. I thoroughly enjoyed my trip from the beginning to the end. The tour guides were very knowledgeable especially in Agra and Jaipur. They were able to answer all questions asked and they knew the best spots for photographs. I have recommended Mr Parveen to my friend who wants to do the same tour next year. This was my first trip to India but it won’t be my last, it has completely surpassed my expectations.
reviews.title: Golden Triangle

reviews.text:
We have been blown away by the service that Sushil has shown over the last week. We have toured the golden triangle and every step of the way have felt completely safe - locked doors, careful driving and real care for our safety. As two young females travelling India this was hugely important for us. Even outside of the car Sushil made sure we were in safe hands always. 
He has educated us on all things India and been so patient with our endless questions! 
Right from the moment we arrived Sushil looked after our experience, nothing was too much trouble, at any time of the day. 
Our first experience of India is one that we will always remember with love laughter and friendship thanks to Sushil. 

Many thanks also to Mukesh, Ali and BK who were fantastic guides over our experience. They really showed us the true India and have such insight into the amazing landmarks
reviews.title: Sushil - the best you could ever wish for!

reviews.text: Me and my friend travelled from England and decided to book a private driver after this being suggested by some other friends that have travelled to India. We arrived in New Delhi to the warmest welcome from our driver Sushil, he absolutely made the trip for us - he was more than a driver, he provided amazing recommendations for food, drinks and activities. We checked our plans with him and he took us on the most logical route, he is a true gent - he drove so safely, checked on us when we got to our hotels, had fresh water and a clean air conditioned vehicle for us every day. The other guides provided by DIBC (Makesh, Ali and BK) were all fabulous and made our trip to a hectic country beyond amazing! Cannot thank Sushil and the guides enough, I would recommend this service to any friend or family member. Thank you so so so much!! We love India!!
reviews.title: Best decision we made in India was booking and getting Sushil!!

reviews.text:
We decided to use discover India by car based on trip advisor reviews, and we have not been disappointed. Our driver, Mr Parveen has 25 years experience of driving and we felt in safe hands. He was a calm, confident driver, very punctual, friendly and courteous. There was always chilled water available in the car and the car was kept spotlessly clean from day 1 to day 10. Mr Parveen's knowledge of the area was invaluable; he was able to suggest places to visit and recommend places to eat, which greatly added to our trip.
We used guides for several visits to the Taj Mahal, Agra Fort, Fatehpur Sikri and the Amber Fort. The guides helped to negotiate the queues ( and sellers pushing their wares) and were very knowledgeable.  Discover India by car arranged the guides on request for us only the day before.
Having a driver meant that we were able to fit in so much more than we could have otherwise done using public transport, visit sites off the beaten track, and rest in a comfortable air conditioned car in between visits. I would highly recommend this service. They are also quick to respond to any queries.
reviews.title: Fantastic Delhi-Udaipur trip with Mr Parveen

reviews.text:
Dimple and Bunty showed us how to make delicious vegetarian dishes. We started with chai then made two curries a Dahl, cumin rice and chapati. 

Dimple also gave us her delicious biscuits, green chilli and Indian dessert. As well as extra chapati cooked with spices and poppadoms! Dimple leads the cooking and is the expert chef while Bunty explains more detail about the dishes. Dimple got us involved and helped show us skills like keeping the chapatis round. 

This is an intimate and informative cooking class. You are in their home and it feels very welcoming and comfortable. It is great value for money. We went at 10am and left at 12. Don't eat  before!! You will be so full. 

Dimple gave us extra cookies and jewellery as a leaving gift. 
Bunty sends the recipes afterwards so you can recreate them at home. 

They also have a homestay apartment. It's much cheaper than where we stayed. If you can book there to stay aswell! It has a cool rooftop and the apartment is huge!!
reviews.title: A unique and welcoming cooking experience with Dimple and Bunty

reviews.title: Very authentic experience - loved it

reviews.text:
I highly recommend the Pink City Cooking Class with Dimple, Bhoomi and family, I had the most fantastic time. The whole family was so warm and welcoming, and I immediately felt like I was at home and part of the family.

Dimple was very knowledgeable and passionate about Indian cooking, and had a fantastic collection of fresh ingredients and spices that smelt incredible.

She guided me through a number of dishes with great expertise - we made masala chai, butter masala paneer, aubergine potato curry, chapati and poppadoms. 

What I appreciated most about the class was the emphasis on using authentic ingredients and traditional cooking techniques. The hands-on nature of the class allowed us to not only learn but also enjoy the process of cooking.

The highlight was when we tasted the dishes we had prepared. The flavors were simply outstanding, and I couldn't believe I had created such delicious food. The intricate flavors really transported me to the heart of India, and tasted far better than the food from restaurants.

Overall, the Indian cooking class was a fantastic experience. I left with a deeper appreciation for Indian cuisine and the confidence to recreate these dishes at home. I highly recommend this class to anyone who wants to explore the flavors of India in a fun and interactive way. I would definitely go back, and next time I am in Jaipur I would love to stay at their homestay as well.

Thank you all for such a wonderful experience!
reviews.title: The best Indian cooking class ever!!

reviews.text: Our tour guide Zozo was wonderful. So much information!!  This is a FULL day tour. You get a taste of each site. Zozo did a great job giving us as much time as possible to see everything.  There’s just not enough time available for Windsor and Bath. But well worth it to get a taste and see where you would want to return when have time to spend. Could easily spend whole day at Windsor and whole day (or 2) in Bath. Had a great time.  Our driver Christian was also great making sure we got everywhere on time. Thank you!! Merry Christmas
reviews.title: Great full day tour

reviews.text: Great tour. Eugene was a fantastic guide. He was very knowledgeable and gave great tips. We also encountered some unforeseen difficulties on the road due to road closures caused by an accident, and Eugene was exceptionally patient and helpful. Highly recommend. But note that you get very limited time at each location (that’s the nature of this kind of tour). Just barely enough to snap some pictures and do a quick walk through. If you would like to spend more time, I would recommend taking the train from London and doing day trips to Bath and Windsor, which are easily worth a whole day.
reviews.title: Many thanks to Eugene

reviews.text: More time spent on bus than at the actual places. Windsor castle didn’t open on time which delayed the time there, basically had to run through it to see it. This isn’t the tours fault though as they can’t control them opening the castle. Every time we were actually at the location it felt very rushed to actually be able to see it. I’d do it on my own so you don’t have to deal with other people being late and loading a bus full again.
reviews.title: Fine

reviews.text: Great experience! Went there with my family and everyone really enjoyed it. It is quite a long day, but it is well worth it to all of these amazing places.
reviews.title: Awesome day

reviews.text:
I booked this tour based on 5 star rating but was a little apprehensive.  Usually, I take time the time to do a little more research but his time I did none.  

We saw a lot! And, they did it in such a way that I wasn't exhausted (and my wife, who usually gets tired before me...she didn't get tired at all!).   I'm not sure of the magic they used but our tour guide and driver were fantastic.   At every site, I thought I saw just enough and then it was on to see something new.  I'd recommend the Pub lunch too.  Food was good and then...some side tours of Harry Potter movie scenes and other areas of interest.  

I would not hesitate to just order another Premium Tours.  In fact, I'm using that as one of my booking criteria.  I feel like I stumbled on to a good thing and I'm going to use them again when we're back.
reviews.title: I feel like I stumbled onto a good thing...

reviews.text: Very knowledgeable guide without assistance from notes. Very attentive to time. Got places as promised and with time to see things. Audio system in bus could use some tweaking; too much bass and volume at times.
reviews.title: A Great Trip

reviews.text:
Nick and Lamar were wonderful hosts on this tour.
Nick had way more information to impart than I expected.
They made the tour run seamlessly.
reviews.title: Great trip

reviews.text:
While it was a lot to do in 1 day.. this tour would have been so much better in the summer months because of having more daylight. 

Even with that.  We had a great time.  Saw and visited some amazing sites, learned a little lore and had a really great dinner. 

Truly a 5 star tour.
reviews.title: Great tour to see really great sites!!

reviews.text:
This was a GREAT tour
Very well organized 
Right amount of time to see the Queen Mary doll house and state rooms and St George chapel at Windsor, time to walk around Stonehenge, eat in Locock ( delicious food by the way, we got the quiche , fish and chips, burger) and Bath
Started at 7.45am  ended at 8.30pm 
It’s the perfect tour for families because the kids rest while on the bus between stops and they don’t walk around for hours like they would do in a museum, my kids are 12-12-10 and it would have been ideal also for primary school children.
Our guide Eugene was superb, very informative and knowledgeable about the history and the locations but also very practical regarding restrooms and small details that a visitor could miss.
Our driver Ricardo was impeccable in his driving
The bus is new, double decker, clean and I truly recommend this tour.
It is NOT the tour for you if you are the person that wants to get a audio guide at every church or museum and like to read every single thing
Price is also very fair
reviews.title: Great tour totally worth it

reviews.text: The bus driver and tour guide were awesome. This group has this down pat and the guide was very knowledgeable. Unfortunately, we learned that morning that we would not be having lunch but having dinner provided instead.  The town of Lacock where we had dinner would be lovely to see, but it was pitch dark when we arrived. We also had thought we would have access to Bath, which we did not.  It is a great tour, but a very long day (13 hours).  You get just over an hour at each location for exploring before moving on, the guide does not go into the location with the group, but gets you there and explains beforehand.  Thankful we did the tour, but I would choose a much shorter one in the future.
reviews.title: Great tour - but long day!

reviews.text: Our tour guide Eugene and driver Ricardo brought our tour to life! Eugene gave us so much history and insight to what we were visiting in a most enjoyable way! The sites themselves were amazing to visit but wouldn’t have been nearly as much fun without Eugene. We had ample time at each location and were clearly directed as to where to be and when. We absolutely recommend this tour with Premium Tours!
reviews.title: Amazing driver & tour guide - spectacular tour experience!

reviews.text:
Our guide Nicholas and driver Robert were both great. Nicholas was very knowledgeable and funny and made the tour a great trip. Windsor Castle and Bath were both beautiful. 

My only recommendation is that during the winter, the pub lunch/dinner option isn’t necessary as it’s dark by the time you get to the town and it’s hard to see much. I would recommend going without that in order to get some more time at the other sites, but other than that it was a great time!
reviews.title: Worthwhile and a lot of fun!

reviews.text: Friendly, knowledgeable, attentative guide and competent driver (thanks Frank and Christian). Lovely historic pub for dinner. Would recommend!
reviews.title: Great day trip to escape busy London.

reviews.text:
Seeing Stonehenge in person was amazing. 
Frank the tour guide was memorable!
Bus driver drove fast. Some friends felt a little queasy.
reviews.title: Great time!

reviews.text:
Frank our tour guide was
Amazing. Knowledgeable informative and great sense of humor. He kept us on track and all had a very good experience.
reviews.title: You must do this tour!

reviews.text: We had a fantastic time on this trip! It was my first time in England and this trip was very entertaining, also incredibly informative. I feel that I got to experience a good bit of the country in one day. Our tour guide Frank was a delight, so quick witted and pleasant. I would absolutely recommend this trip to anyone interested in a good day’s excursion.
reviews.title: All day trip to Windsor Castle, Stonehenge, and Bath.

reviews.text: Nicholas (our guide) and Robert (our driver) made the trip easy, fun and memorable. Nicholas shared his knowledge of the history and culture of each area and his wit was entertaining. It’s a full day trip but allows plenty of rest in the coach between stops.
reviews.title: A Must-Do When in London

reviews.text: The landmarks selected for this tour did not disappoint! Windsor Castle had so many artworks and artifacts, Stonehenge and the countryside were so much more than I expected, and while I have been to Bath before, having Nicholas explain more and narrate our trip added so much more to the experience. Robert and Nicholas were incredible! Nicholas is very funny and knowledgeable of everything along the route, and both he and Robert kept us on time, so we enjoyed each stop thoroughly. I can not recommend them enough!
reviews.title: A Week Worth of Landmarks in a Single Day

reviews.text: This was a wonderful long day tour! Steve, our guide, and driver Leon, we’re incredible! Seriously, Leon was the best. Super friendly, welcoming, and stood up for folks who didn’t have a voice. Leon deserves all the recognition!
reviews.title: Wonderful coach ride!

reviews.text: Our driver Hadar, and our tour guide Nick, were excellent and made all the difference. We could have tried to drive to these locations on our own but it was invaluable getting all the history and valuable advice and information from our tour guide before we arrived at each destination. I was also very happy that although there were several accidents on the motorway, our expert driver was able to mostly keep us on schedule and safely get us where we needed to go even though I wondered how he would be able to fit such a large double decker bus through some of the village towns and roads. This was the highlight of our London trip even though we booked it last minute
reviews.title: Excellent value, highlight of our trip

reviews.text: This was my first visit to India for a short solo trip & I wanted to see all the big sights in Delhi & this tour was perfect. Asim and Ankur were incredibly professional, friendly, and arranged everything with ease while being incredibly knowledgeable along the way. I would highly recommend this tour to anyone visiting Delhi.
reviews.title: A great way to see the highlights of Delhi

reviews.text: Amazing door to door service. Every single thing is taken care of with multiple people working in concert at multiple venues. Asim was a great guide and Vishnu a safe driver.
reviews.title: Delhi in a day

reviews.text: Asim was an excellent and flexible tour guide. He showed us part of Old and New Delhi we wouldn’t have otherwise seen. The transport was clean, new and air conditioned. We had a comfortable and pleasant day touring. Highly recommend!
reviews.title: Excellent tour

reviews.text:
My family and I had a wonderful experience spent in Delhi thanks to guide Sujal who led us through a day of memorable visits to historical & cultural places. We rode auto-rickshaws through Old Delhi neighborhoods, walked through Chandni Chowk, ate some jalebis, saw the Red Fort. Sujal took great to ensure the comfort of my family, who found the experience unforgettable. Sujal discussed various options with us to customize the tour to our satisfaction and based on his input, we decided to skip Qutub Minar and visit Akshardham temple instead - it was amazing! Sujal was very informative and courteous and prioritized the needs of our family when I told him our kids needed to eat lunch first before continuing the tour . Sujal took us to an excellent lunch spot before we rounded out the tour at Humayan's tomb. 
We we were also very happy with the tour management who accommodated our last minute request to add 2 more local family members to the tour - they handled it quickly and got us a bigger & very comfortable vehicle. The driver Seva Ram was also very polite & accommodating when we had to take a slight detour to pick up the family members.
Overall, an amazing, memorable experience that I would highly recommend!
reviews.title: Amazing, customized & memorable experience with informative, friendly & attentive guide!

reviews.text:
Sujal was a great tour guide by foot, car and Tuktuk. We liked the market and the mosque the most. It was nice to start early in the morning to see the city wake up. Sujal was full of insightful stories about the monuments and made the experience that much special.
None of the entrance fees are actually included in this price. We paid our guide the tickets at the end.
reviews.title: Short and Sweet New & Old Delhi

reviews.text: An amazing first day in India. We were treated to a myriad of beautiful historical buildings, markets, and classy local stores including world class tea store and Kashmir textile store. Our experienced guide Arvind knew all of the historical stories behind the sites we visited, and ensured we felt safe at all times. Our driver Ajay was wonderful too and we honestly would give this trip experience 11/10 if we could. We stuffed up the location for pick up and due to our own mistake our driver and guide went to the wrong hotel. They were so patient and accomodating to us despite this. My female friend who I travelled with also loved having Arvind and Ajay, as she felt very safe in their company. Please do yourself a favour and book.
reviews.title: New Delhi Delights

reviews.text: Sujal was a knowledgeable guide who was flexible for the needs of our large family group ranging in ages from 4 to 50. He made sure to tell us lots of interesting stories about each of the sights we visited. He expertly navigated crowded areas and made majestic locales in Delhi memorable. Highly recommend!
reviews.title: Don't miss a Delhi tour with Sujal!

reviews.text: A really great day learning about New Delhi on this half day tour. Both Sujal and the driver Arun were courteous and professional
reviews.title: Great day

reviews.text: We are a young family from Australia that has been to India several times. We decided to take the tour to make things easier for our family to navigate our stay. Lalit was a great tour guide, picked us up from our hotel and coordinated the entire day of visits including all tour entrances. It was completely hassle free. The visit to Jama Masjid and Old Delhi was one of the best experiences we have ever had. An amazing day and totally worth it rather than trying to navigate this yourself.
reviews.title: The best way to see Delhi

reviews.text: Amazing experience! Our guide happi was so knowledgeable and lovely. We learnt so much not just about the places we saw but also about the history and culture in India
reviews.title: Amazing experience

reviews.text: Excellent guide (Nawin), who provided lots of historical detail and context. The driver (Rahul) was courteous and efficient
reviews.title: Great tour of Delhi!

reviews.text: We had a wonderful time at our tour! Asim was one of the best tour guides we have ever had. He is very knowledgeable about the history of Old and New Delhi and made sure we had a comfortable and great time. I would recommend this tour to everyone who wants to experience Delhi firsthand.
reviews.title: Best Tour

reviews.text: I was with Sujal and he was one of the best tour guides ever. Showed us all of the local gems and must sees. Great company and great stories, highly recommend.
reviews.title: New Delhi Tour Experience - Sujal

reviews.text: Had no idea what to do in Delhi. Sujal saved the day, had a top tour in all of Delhi. We would have walked around aimlessly but instead we got a thorough tour of everything you’d want to see in Delhi
reviews.title: Beast tour

reviews.text: Five stars aren't enough to express my gratitude to Sujal for the fantastic 8-hour tour of New Delhi. Sujal's knowledge and enthusiasm for the city made the experience truly remarkable. He went above and beyond to ensure we saw all the key attractions and provided valuable insights throughout the journey. Thank you, Sujal, for making my visit to New Delhi unforgettable!
reviews.title: Beyond expectations

reviews.text: Great moment discovering Delhi soth my guide who speaks Kuldeep excellent French: very intersting anecdotes on India History
reviews.title: Great experience

reviews.text: Great short old Delhi tour. Booked last minute. Thanks for being flexible also with the timing suggestions. A beautiful experience, I felt safe throughout. The guide was friendly and knowledgeable. Can absolutely recommend.
reviews.title: Old Delhi half day.

reviews.text: Nawin, our guide, transformed tour for my family of 7  into an extraordinary experience. His blend of knowledge, charisma, and enthusiasm brought history and culture to life, making each location memorable with his stories and insights. Not just a storyteller, Nawin’s engaged everyone, answering questions with patience, ensuring all felt included. His dynamic style mixed education and entertainment, keeping us enthralled. Nawin is more than a guide; he's a master storyteller, a skilled photographer, and an excellent host, creating a deeply connected and unforgettable experience. 👍🏽💯
reviews.title: An Unforgettable Journey with an Exceptional Guide!

reviews.text: Rumy Khan is our guide for the entire day and our experience is superb. We have enjoyed his company greatly. Thanks for such a nice experience.

reviews.text: Rumi khan  has good knowledge of the most monuments and Well explain during the day. Overall good experience

Clean and comfortable vehicle. The guides truly made our experience memorable. Highly recommend for those visiting India on a shorter length of duration!
reviews.title: Extremely kind guides, excellent hotels, comprehensive sightseeing!

reviews.text: A great trip and perfect length for seeing all you want to see in the golden triangle. We had great guides and our driver Anil was the best! Can’t recommend this enough.
reviews.title: Great trip to the golden triangle!

reviews.text: Everything was well arranged and I did not have to worry about anything. The person who did the coordination updated me with info and answered my questions. Driver was careful and patient. Guides were professional. Overall a very enjoyable trip.
reviews.title: Golden Triangle Tour in India

reviews.text:
My sincere thanks to Amit Narang from Crystal India Holidays for making my trip with family a memorable one. 
Rajinder ji, our tour driver was one of the nicest humans and also the best and safest drivers. 
The guides in all locations were very friendly, entertaining and knowledgeable. 5 stars to them!! 
The hotels- Jaypee Palace and Novotel were amazing. 
The whole experince was fabulous and comfortable and truly unforgettable for my mom and dad! 
I recommend this to all!
reviews.title: Thank you for an amazing private tour!

reviews.text: Visiting Taj Mahal was the highlight of the trip. Jaipur was enjoyable experience.The driver Vickey and local guides were excellent with great communication skills. The whole trip was enjoyable and comfortable with elderly parents and Adult children
reviews.title: Wonderful Trip

reviews.text: We had a fantastic time on this tour, from the itinerary and attractions to the driver and local guides. It was awe inspiring to see the Taj Mahal. Highly recommend.
reviews.title: Once in a lifetime trip

reviews.text: Fantastic trip . Company was amazing. Driver was really friendly with our family. Guides were so good.
reviews.title: Fantastic Trip

reviews.text:
What can i say, this whole trip was amazing. I opted for the 5 star hotel stay and for me it was worth it. 

First and foremost, my driver Prithi who was with me for the 4 days was an absolute legend. Not only was he very professional, he was also very funny and went out of his way to make me comfortable and take me anywhere I wanted to go if time permitted. The car ride was very comfortable and the car itself was kept spotless with plenty of water aboard if you ever feel parched.

My guides Naveen (Delhi), Dharvinder (Jaipur) &
Arif (Agra) were very knowledgeable, passionate and professional in their work. Also don’t get fooled into getting a professional photographer especially at the Taj Mahal. All 3 guides are practically professional photographers themselves. They know all the instagram spots for a great photo. Giving me directions on how to pose to give me the best photos possible. Cannot recommend this tour enough so if you’re looking at this tour, do yourself a favour and book it in. Thanks once again to the whole team, you made my trip to India very memorable and one I won’t forget anytime soon. All the best :)
reviews.title: India Fast Tracked

reviews.text: We had visited 3 places with 3 different guides. The first is Nave in New Delhi. He was in hurry and made us confused. Arif was our guide in Agra. He is very knowlegeable. We had an impressive day at Taj Mahal and Agra Fort. Yozi was the guide in Jaipur. He is very good at taking photos. In a word, they organized the trip very smoothly. No hassle. Highly recommend.
reviews.title: Impressive Journey

reviews.text: A great introduction to the Golden Triangle. Thanks to our excellent guides (Nitin in Delhi, Afit in Agra and Pawan in Jaipur) we learned so much about the rich history of India. I really recommend this tour as a stress-free way to see these amazing sights. You won't be able to see everything, of course, but you will cover the main attractions. A special thank you to our driver, Ravinder, who calmly drove us through the crazy traffic and seemed to magically be waiting whenever we needed him!
reviews.title: A great tour to see the main sights of Golden Triangle

reviews.text:
We had An amazing tour! Each city was an experience. The tour guides were very experienced and gave a lot of information. Also the tour could be tailor made to our wishes and we got to see the Taj Mahal at sunrise. 
We would like to thank our guides: Naresh (Delhi), Akseh (Agra), Pratik (Jaipur). 
Also they were the best photographers and very patient with us three women, during photo sessions & shopping. 
Like a wise men said: “life is like ice cream, enjoy it before it melts” - Sonny always funny (pratik). 
And we would like to give a special shout out to Sohan, our driver. He is a very experienced driver & a human google maps. He also gave us some good tips, like a good massage place. 
The hotels were good quality and in a good area.
reviews.title: Golden time at the golden triangle

reviews.text: Our trip was amazing.  Crystal India tours looked after us well.  Our driver Pritam was very experienced and safe driver who got us to all our destinations on time
reviews.title: Golden triangle 4 day tour Delhi, Agra, Japur, Delhi

reviews.text: Great experience! Outstanding service by the operator! There’s no cons to say as such. Do not more the opportunity. 5 stars.
reviews.title: Outstanding service

reviews.text: This tour is brilliant and well planned.  Amit, the coordinator is on top of it all.  Pritam the driver is punctual, calm and very safe.   It all met my expectations.  The accommodations, the tour guides and timing.   The tour was not overdone, it remained fun & interesting, just enough information that one can still enjoy each moment in every places that is part of the program.  Thank you very much!
reviews.title: India’s true gem!

reviews.text: Tour was great, knowledgeable tour guides for each day who all spoke and understand english well.  Our Driver was absolutely amazing, very kind and helpful, we felt very safe with his driving and understanding our requests.
reviews.title: Fantastic Tour, absolute MUST

reviews.text: Fabulous trip across the most beautiful part of India, the Golden Triangle, exceptionally organized, with great guides and a very professional driver. Highly recommend
reviews.title: The best India experience you can get

reviews.text:
Our driver was great.

The tour could have been better. Tour guide's information to us wasn't factual. Additionally, our guides took us to upcharged tourist souvenir shops that were clearly meant to take advantage of us.

We also learned that travel by car is quite tiresome. I'd recommend traveling by train (you can get first class tickets) and hiring a reputable tour guide.

Our hotels were supposed to be 5 star but we were disappointed by the hotel in agra and jaipur. jaypee palace is clearly a tourist trap. the hilton in jaipur had a strong perfume masking the mildew smell which made our clothes smell for the rest of the trip
reviews.title: Do not book this tour

ownerResponse.text:
We are glad to know that you found the Driver great. We deeply apologise for the inconvenience caused. I would like to inform you that our Guides are approved by Ministry of Tourism, Government of India.

Jaypee Palace is a Government Approved 5 Star Deluxe Hotel and Hilton Jaipur is a Government Approved 5 Star Hotel, you may check reviews of these hotels online as well.

As you wanted us to Book The Oberoi Amarvilas in  Agra and similar hotel in Jaipur, which costs Approximately USD 650 per room per night, so for 3 nights it would be Approximately USD 1950 for 1 room, We told you that we could book those hotels for you but there will be additional charges for that because prices of those hotels are very high, but you said that you want those hotel within the price you paid for the tour, Which was not possible for us because for the Entire tour including Car with Driver, Guides, 5 Star Hotels etc. you paid USD 700 for 2 people. It's very disheartening to see that you are penalizing us this way.

Still we apologize for the inconvenience caused to you.

We hope to see you again in the future.

Best regards,
Golden Triangle Delhi Agra Jaipur Tour / Crystal India Holidays.

reviews.text: Our driver, Jagdish, safely navigated all traffic and answered every question we had about what we were seeing. He was kind and knowledgable and very helpful. Nittin guided us expertly through Delhi with expertise and consideration for what could have felt overwhelming with sights and sounds. The Lotus Temple prayer was exceptional in every way. The TukTuk ride to the Taj Mahal was a wonderfully submersive experience. The Taj was glorious. And Jaipur is a dazzling gem to behold.
reviews.title: Dazzling Sights Where Kindness is King

reviews.text: I wasn't sure what to expect with this tour, but it all went smoothly and was very well organised, so I can definitely recommend it to others. We were picked up from our hotel by our driver, Sohan, who we felt very safe with as passengers throughout the trip. This was important to us as there is a lot of driving between cities. He was very kind, always offering to go above and beyond if we wanted to go anywhere else. There was a different guide each day in each city, and all were friendly and accommodating. The hotels were all fine also.
reviews.title: I wasn't sure what to...

ownerResponse.text:
We are glad to know that you found the tour very well organised, We do our best to provide hassle free services to our each and every guest. 

We hop to see you again.

Best regards,
Team Golden Triangle Delhi Agra Jaipur Tour / Crystal India Holidays.

reviews.text: Absolutely fabulous trip. Madan was a wonderful driver that looked after us for the whole trip, driving safely, stopping for anything we needed and telling us interesting information about sites we passed on the way. Everything was very well organised and efficient, we saw so much in a short time and the guides were very knowledgeable. The hotels were extraordinary. Everything was delightful and we felt very safe and looked after and all our needs were met. We had the best time. Thank you so much! :)
reviews.title: Amazing

reviews.text:
Adil was an excellent guide - he was informative, passionate and always very helpful. The tour ran smoothly and we were able to see multiple sites during the day. The Taj Mahal was incredible - Adil provided lots of information and guidance about the history and conservation. 
Adil was the best guide we've had and looked after us wonderfully.
reviews.title: The best way to see the Taj Mahal

reviews.text: Highly recommended tour.... everything was planned and perfect as expected.  It is a great experience if you one a day trip to Agra.  Also Faizan was very knowledgeable of the place. I really like locals as tour guides.
reviews.title: Perfect day trip to Agra

reviews.text: We were very happy with the tour organised by Pioneer holidays, the whole day went very smoothly.  Our tour guide, Adil Khan, was really good and explained the history of Taj Mahal and other sites. We could not fault the day.
reviews.title: Taj Mahal Tour

reviews.text: Door to door service from Delhi and back. Everything was on time. The trip was efficient, maximized for safety and informative. I've been to the Taj Majal twice before, once as a child and once on my own. This time it was with my wife and three young kids. This was perfect for a family. Shaan was a wonderful guide. Highly recommend.
reviews.title: Flawless day with three young kids in tow

reviews.text: Excellent tour and although it was so crowded Ali took care of us by meticulously planning so we could cover all most important areas and food was also amazing that we stopped. Highly recommend this if you visiting like me and Agra was amazing and memorable trip
reviews.title: Full day tour at Taj

reviews.text: I had a great experience with this tour. Hotel pick up was on time and seamless. The express train was relatively clean but the best part is that it’s the fastest way to get from Delhi to Agra vs driving. Greeted warmly in Agra by my tour guide Moon and the driver. Moon was extremely hospitable and very knowledgeable. I’ll admit I didn’t come to India with a lot knowledge of Its rich history, but I left with a lot of history lessons and memories. Overall, everything was pretty seamless, and I would highly recommend Moon to anyone.
reviews.title: Delhi to Agra full day tour

reviews.text: Day tour of Agra, including the Taj Mahal and Agra Fort.  Nabeel was great—Informative and helped us navigate the attractions with ease.
reviews.title: Agra Tour

reviews.text:
The whole experience of Taj Mahal tour with Pioneer Holidays was amazing from receiving the train ticket confirmations to the car journey on Agra roads to visiting the beautiful Taj Mahal, it was flawless.

We would definitely recommend our tour guide, Adil Khan, he explained everything in detail which made the trip even better.  He is very knowledgeable, our boys and us learned a lot about the sites.
reviews.title: Taj Mahal Tour

reviews.text: Had a great day and well explained by our tour guide Adil Khan. We were picked up from the station and visited the Taj Mahal and the baby Taj.
reviews.title: Great experience in Agra

reviews.text:
Booked with Pioneer Tours on short notice and they were happy to oblige.  We got a wonderful guide in Shan Khan, who was very knowledgeable and helpful all day. 
We were not sure what to expect and once Shan explained the day’s activities we were excited to see everything the Tour had to offer. 
Our driver Pankaj is a very good and safe driver.
reviews.title: Memorable Tour

reviews.text: The service was excellent from the point of booking until we returned back to our house in Delhi. Our guide Adil was so knowledgeable and it was great to see how much pride he takes in his city and its history. We appreciated that he let us customize our tour, so we were able to pick our own lunch spot and also stop (a few times!) for some locally famous clay cup chai. Our drivers Arun and Salman also provided wonderful service. The 2nd AC class was good for the short journey, and we were met with a personal pickup and drop off in the train car at both ends of the trip. Definitely recommend this service to anyone looking for a completely stress-free Agra experience.
reviews.title: Enjoyable and super easy Agra experience

reviews.text: From start to finish the trip was very well planned out and relatively hassle free. We had the same driver to and from the station in Delhi. Faizan met us off the train with another driver in Agra and made the whole process to the Taj Mahal very easy with organising tickets, being a great tour guide, organising lunch, the fort tour and more. Faizan is extremely knowledgeable with the history of all the landmarks and we learnt loads from him.
reviews.title: Great day trip to the Taj Mahal

reviews.text: Selamat was very helpful in organizing everything end to end. Sent me a message to let me know train to Agra in the morning was booked out and would arrange economy class seat instead. I told him I would prefer to go by car in that case and he arranged it. The car which came was nice and clean and the driver Rahul was very courteous. Upon arriving in Agra we met our guide Imran, who was very knowledgeable being a local from there for 3 generations. He took us around Taj Mahal, explained everything patiently, helped us take pictures at the right viewpoints. Was more than happy to answer any questions. We then had lunch which was good with starters served at the table then a buffet with a large variety of offerings. We picked up the local petha and dalmoth (locally famous sweets and snacks) from Gopal Das and Panchi stores, you can try before buying there. We were then taken to a marble emporium where they do inlay work just like how it’s done at Taj Mahal. Learning about the process and then browsing through the pieces available was eye-opening as it’s a dying craft globally. Pieces were really beautiful. Last stop was Agra Fort before Imran and Rahul dropped us to our train. Imran came right up till we were seated on the train and a pre-arranged driver picked us up from where we arrived in Delhi. Selamat was in touch the whole time to make sure everything was going fine. Would highly recommend this package.
reviews.title: Well organized, smooth end-to-end experience

reviews.text: I had a great tour of the Taj Mahal and the Agra fort with Farid Baig.  His knowledge was amazing and he was both organized and professional.  He was flexible and always checking if the tour was meeting my expectations.  He spoke English very well and it was as if I was on a tour with a friend.  Lunch was also quite good.  Over all, a great trip.  As well, the driver I had was excellent, but I forgot his name.  The drive was from Delhi and is a lot of driving for just one day.
reviews.title: An Excellent Tour of Taj Mahal

reviews.text: Farid was a fantastic tour guide. Traveling alone, safety is always my first priority and I always felt that Farid was looking out for me. reviews.text: We went to Agra on Jan 21st, an extremely foggy day. The train left on time but took over 4 hours to reach due to fog. Fortunately, the fog cleared just as we got there. We met our guide Farid on the platform. The Taj is really spectacular but Farid’s explanations and commentaries are what makes this tour really worth it. Agra fort is also great and impressive. Because we were very late getting to Agra we ended up going for lunch late afternoon and we honestly found that the BBQ-buffet was average at best, with little options. Also, the tour was supposed to include a visit to baby Taj, which was never mentioned. It would not have made a difference because we probably would have skipped it. The train back being delayed at least 4 hours, we opted to return by car and also had to skip the visit to the stone workers shop in order to reach Delhi at a reasonable hour. Overall an amazing experience with some slight annoyance caused by the weather.
reviews.title: Amazing visit
