I was recommended to IndianCircle by my sister-in-law who had met the owner as part of a larger tour a couple years back. 

I was on my own in Delhi in transit to/from Dharamshala. IndianCircle assigned a tour guide and driver to me, and I couldn't have been happier :-). 

They took me to do what I wanted to do (a street shave, tailor a blazer, eat local and visit work colleagues, too), showed me places and things they knew I would enjoy (Lotus, Vishnu and Jain temples and Old Delhi market), put me in a most comfortable 4*hotel (Nüo), and picked me up and dropped me virtually door to door at intl and domestic airports and train stations to/from the Northeast. 

I cannot recommend them enough. 

As soon as they get an easy online credit card deposit and final payment system going (which admittedly, is tough for non-Indian credit cards), it will make things even easier and more comfortable for both parties, tourist and tour company. Am certain they will sort this out soon. 

Enjoy your visit to India with IndianCircle!

reviews.text:
This review should be read in full since there are both pros and cons.  
Pros -
1.  Viv was our tour guide and she was amazing!  So incredibly personable and knowledgeable of all things food, wine, and the area!
2.  The food was absolutely incredible, I actually went back to one of the restaurants after the tour because I was craving the one dish so much but the service was terrible (but not for the tour).
3.  The wine and scenery were also amazing!
Cons -
Left hungry - see
We knew another couple that eats about the same amount as we do and they left very full (different tour).  I am not sure why but we were not full at all.  I think this tour was arranged especially for us since the one we originally scheduled was cancelled.  
First place we each got a glass of sparkling wine and a cheese board to split.  I am sure the cheeses were expensive and they were delicious - just not a lot of food.
Second place only one glass of wine was ordered and that was split between my husband and I.  We had the most incredible clam chowder that I ever had (that is what we went back for) and we each got a normal serving.
Third place again - one serving of wine split between the two of us and one entre split between us and an order of flat bread split.
Forth and final - again split the port wine, split a dessert.
We figured out that that the company made $255 after food, wine and tip.  I understand it is a business - again - we thoroughly enjoyed it, just would have liked a little more food and wine.  
Our tour guide was so incredibly sweet and gave us so much helpful advise...Hope this helps.  Forgot to take a picture of the cheese board.
reviews.title: Great experience, loved the food and wine but left a little hungry

ownerResponse.text: Thank you for your thoughtful review. This is the first time since 2016 that I am hearing not enough food though. We are very clear in our marketing that everyone receives a half a glass of wine at each four stops. We buy the food like normal customers, pay tax and 20% tip. I can promise you we do not make $255, if only.  As a matter of fact, we loose money on two people tours, but I did not want to cancel since you had already been moved.  It seems like overall you had a good experience, and for that Viv and I are both happy!

reviews.text: We visited 4 Sonoma locations during a 3 hour tour.  Our first stop was at a lovely restaurant, The Girl and The Fig, where we enjoyed delicious cheese, fig compote and yummy Quiche Lorraine.  The food was paired with a JCB No. 69, 2016 Sparkling Brut Rosé and the girl & the fig, 2017 Rosé.  The second stop was at FIGONE OLIVE OIL CO. where we had the opportunity to take amazing olive oils and balsamic vinegars. This family owned business grows olives in the nearby San Joaquin Valley.  Our third stop was at The Delhi Belly Indian Bistro.  The extraordinary Indian creations were paired with Cline Viognier wine.  Our last stop was at a tasting room for a specialty, high-end wine company, Galatea Effect, where we enjoyed several wines from their Conoscenti collection.  Renee was a great host, was very knowledgeable about both the foods and wines that she arranged.  We loved the tour and would do it again.

Amazing half-day tour to discover the main qatari landmarks in North Qatar. From old pearl fishing village in Jumail, to historical military gort in Zubarah and mangroves in Pearl Island. Ideal to have a beautiful overview of the Gulf country. Strongly recommended.

reviews.text: Wonderful trip with Asim ! The camels were the best part of the day!! Could not believe how many camels there were and they were so cute ! We liked the fish market too. Was great to know how regulated the industry is for consumer safety. The desert was vast and formations very cool for photos. Would definitely recommend this day trip to see some other parts of the country. Great for all ages. We traveled with 2 adults and one preteen.

reviews.text: ASIM was a great guide. Our day was fun, educational and entertaining. You’ll see parts of Qatar you would not see otherwise. Go ahead, book it!

reviews.text: Great mix of historical towns and places with stunning natural landscapes and a bit of leisure pastimes added to the mix. Our Guide was so good !!

reviews.text:
I booked this private tour to discover North and West Qatar which by far has been one of the best experiences I’ve ever had.

Guides Azim and Junaid together went to lengths to make sure I had the most exceptional experience.

I saw the most stunning places, forts, beaches and at the mushroom formations I was literally lost for words.

Sculptures by Richard Serra were very interesting and the history behind it was fascinating.

Later in the tour I had time to spend at the mangroves which I really enjoyed and throughout the tour I learned so much from Azim and Junaid. They were both so much fun to be with and honestly couldn’t believe where all the time went.
reviews.title: Experience of a lifetime

reviews.text: Our tour guide Sajid was really friendly and knowledgeable and we got to see some really cool things
reviews.title: Amazing trip

reviews.text: We had a great day sightseeing in Qatar with Asim. He was very knowledgeable and  answered all of our questions that we had for him. I really feel like he wanted to make sure we all had a great time and we did! I would definitely recommend this tour
reviews.title: Great tour

reviews.text: We enjoyed the sites we visited, it was a nice overview of past and present. Our guide/driver was really more of a driver.   He was very kind and took us to all of the scheduled places and kindly took pictures of us. He was a good driver and the vehicle was sound and safe. We could not have visited all the sights we saw without a knowledgable driver. But it appeared that he hadn’t been fully trained as a guide per se. We asked a lot of questions, but there was little historical narrative or information shared without the questions we asked. Overall, we enjoyed our tour but would encourage his company to invest in training for the actual “guiding” element of the tour.
reviews.title: Good overview tour that could use guiding element improvements

reviews.text: Thanks to Sajid we spent a lovely, interesting and also funny day in North and West Qatar. We had very good and lively conversations about life in Qatar. Sajid knows a lot about history, culture and locals. He drove carefully and spent extra time to show us some of our desired places. We highly recommend the tour to Al Khor, Purple Island, Al Zubara, Zekreet and some more places. Qatar is an impressive - still unspoilt - country.
reviews.title: Discovering the roots of Qatar

reviews.text: I had an amazing time with Asim. He is very reliable, flexible and takes the time to explain what you’re looking at. I highly recommend taking this tour; you will see a lot of the diverse sights of Qatar.
reviews.title: Highly recommended

reviews.text: An excellent comprehensive overview of Qatar.  Asim was very knowledgeable and provided me with a wealth of information.  Highly recommended.

reviews.text: This was a very complete and comprehensive tour of both the Doha city as well as the central and northern countryside. Our tour guide Zain was very knowledgeable and excellent and very accommodating as we requested to either shorten or lengthen the various stops throughout the day. Mostly we shortened the planned stops as we wanted to return to our ship by 4pm, but it is nice to know that they are willing to give you plenty of time as needed. We would highly recommend Zain.
reviews.title: An amazing full-day tour with Zain of the highlights of Doha city and the Qatar northern regions

reviews.text: This was a great tour, packed full of wonderful sights from the city to the desert! Our tour guide was Sajid Khan, who was informative, kind, and considerate. He was always glad to stop to allow us to take a photo whenever we wished. A fun highlight for this particular tour was seeing the fishing industry up north, and the amazing market that contained wonderful varieties of freshly caught fish. Sajid was flexible with regard to our itinerary. When we arrived in the morning, the Museum of Islamic Arts was closed so we saw other things first and went back to the museum later. We had a delightful walk along a mangrove trail, where we saw lots of little crabs scampering about. What a surprise to see this in the desert! The architecture of Doha is breathtaking, and Sajid knew the best spots to view each building. All in all, a lovely trip.
reviews.title: You get to see it all!

reviews.text: Aasim was a courteous and knowledgeable about the history of Qatar. He is great guide. Enjoyed the day trip.
reviews.title: Good tour

reviews.text: Amazing private tour. Asim was a terrific tour guide.  He was knowledgeable and we really had a good understanding of the north of the country as well as the city of Doha.  It really opened my eyes to the outstanding accomplishments of this young country.  There are two optional museum stops in this tour but we had run out of steam at the end of the day.  Water and tea were provided during the tour but there was no stop for lunch and it can be a long tour so eat a hearty breakfast.
reviews.title: GREAT day in Qatar.

reviews.text: ASIM our driver was amazing. He was prompt and very knowledgeable about Qatar. We visited the northern areas and the city. ASIM went out of his way to customize the tour to our needs. I totally recommend this tour. It was a great day and super to learn more about the history and city and culture.
reviews.title: Great day in Qatar!

reviews.text: On this Middle East trip we've booked four private tours just for Tina and me. Three of our drivers called themselves "guides" but without talking to us!  And then there was Ali on this all-day, first-impression tour of Qatar and the surrounding areas. The moment we got into his car, Ali felt like a family member and related to us as if we were his parents or aunt or uncle. Any and all questions we asked were answered with honesty, sincerity and details about his life and culture and history of the region. This man became the highlight of the excursion and we will never forget him. If you book this tour or others by Golden Adventures Qatar, ask for Ali.
reviews.title: When you book this tour, ask for Ali!

reviews.text: It was indeed a pleasure for us to be guided by Asim! He was very professional, courteous and quite informative. Even though our time was short, Asim made us appreciate the pride, beauty and splendor of the nation of Qatar!
reviews.title: Great experience

reviews.text: A very convenient way to make the most out of a layover. Salman was able to safely take me around North Qatar and back to busy Doha, with a sprinkling of local knowledge. It was good to see the heritage of Qatar but moreso, the current wonders all wrapped in a neat package.
reviews.title: Enjoyed this layover tour of Qatar

reviews.text: We set off from Doha with our tour guide Khalid  from doha tourism  in a good air conditioned car. Our first stop was Al Khor, which is a fishing village. We were too late to see the fisherman with their catch but viewed the harbour. We headed to the World heritage Al Zubara fort and then Al Jumail archaeological site and then on to Al Shamal to experience local food in a local restaurant. The temperature was very hot (about 40 degrees) but we still enjoyed the experience. If you are interested in knowing more about Qatari history this is a good tour to get to know Khalid  was a wealth of information and a good ambassador for this company.
reviews.title: Great experience

reviews.text:
What can we say? Just back to the ship after spending the best day with Anwar our guide! 
Needless to say that we will 100% be returning to Qatar after his tour and enthusiasm. We did the 4 hours and Anwar was so happy to accommodate anything we needed and very aware of the fact that we had young children and made the tour fun…. He even paid for my son to get candy floss as we didn’t have cash on us. So very grateful! 
We booked at 11pm on 23rd and met Anwar at 11am on 24th Christmas Eve. 
Such professionalism and easy to book and pay.
We have already recommended to friends coming to Qatar and will be returning as soon as possible.
Thanks team!

Your tour encourages us to come back to Qatar for another visit in the future.

reviews.text: Really great and attentive driver and guides. Driver Radish was driving really safe, never got unsafe in any way and we could stop and buy food/bathroom whenever and however long we wanted. Got to see the most important sites in the golden triangle with knowledgable guides and also saw a tiger very close! Also since it was private guide and driver it was flexible. For example, one of us got a little sick (unrelated to the trip, chronic issues) and it was no problem to stay a little longer at the hotel and be picked up later while others could go on that days tour. Would definitely recommend anyone who want to see all the important sites without any hassle!
reviews.title: Excellent!

reviews.text:
It was a well coordinated trip with fantastic Nek, driving the whole 4 days.  He was a safe driver in crazy traffic, very accommodating and flexible.  We really felt he looked after us.  Each guide of the city days we had great English speaking guides.  There is a lot of driving, lots!  If you can afford an extra day, stay extra in Jaipur.
No tigers- requested small jeep for morning safari.  Didn’t have high expectations, but saw interesting landscape and other animals
reviews.title: Nek- best driver ever!!!

reviews.text: Amazing trip!! Saw lots of amazing places. Was very well organized and very friendly. Definitely recommend!!

reviews.text: This trip was amazing! We went with six people, and it’s an absolute must if you are visiting India and only have a small amount of time. The driver Chain Singh was amazing and got us safely to every destination. All of the tour guides in each of the cities were very knowledgeable, and happy to answer all questions. Only sad thing was that we didn’t get to see tigers in Ranthambhore but that’s because we did a morning safari versus an evening safari (apparently you are more likely to see them in the evening). We chose to stay at all five star hotels and they were all absolutely stunning. Clean, beautiful, well-kept, and great beds. The staff was very helpful. Breakfast included in the hotels was plentiful.
reviews.title: An absolute must

reviews.text: This tour was amazing! It’s a busy four days but well worth it. We went to pretty much every stop as promised, and everything we saw was exceptional. Ranthambore is stunning regardless of whether you see a tiger (we did!) and worth the drive. The hotels were great (especially the Jaypee Palace and The Tigress). It is a light itinerary in Delhi comprising mostly of places on the outskirts of town, so I’d suggest an extra day or two in Delhi which we planned for. Our driver Kamal was a fantastic driver with a very comfortable car- he was really an additional guide with so much information! Our guides in each city were quite good too. Can’t recommend this tour enough!
reviews.title: Excellent tour- Must go!

ownerResponse.text:
We are thrilled that you saw a Tiger at Ranthambore National Park. if our guest would like to visit more places in Delhi then we could add it without any additional charges. We hope to see you again in the future.

Best regards,
Team Golden Triangle Delhi Agra Jaipur Tour / Crystal India Holidays.

reviews.text: Hits all the highlights.  A great value.  Driver and guides were wonderful.  We were able to enjoy are trip stress free……..
reviews.title: Trip was great.  Driver and guides were top notch.   Well worth the value.  I highly recommend

reviews.text: My driver, Prithi, was excellent. So helpful and considerate, and also a good conversation partner during some of the longer driving stretches. The local guides were all very good as well. The hotels were all high quality -- I particularly enjoyed the hotels in Agra and Ranthambore (wasn't as big a fan of the Radisson in Jaipur - too sterile and westernized, though perfectly clean and nice). Agra was incredible, and the highlight of the trip - the Taj Mahal is everything it's cracked up to be, and the Agra Fort was great as well. Jaipur was lovely also, especially the Jantar Mantar and Amber Fort / Mirror Palace. The safari in Ranthambore was a little disappointing, in that we saw no tigers and in fact no wildlife that I couldn't see at home in the U.S. It was also a long drive to get to Ranthambore and back. But it was still enjoyable and interesting, and the hotel there is great. Overall, Crystal Tours of India delivered what they promised, and it was a great way to do sightseeing in northern India.
reviews.title: Great tour!

reviews.text: I can only confirm all the other fantastic reviews of this tour. The driver was really outstanding and gave us a fantastic time since we spend quite a lot time in the car. The local guides are really knowledgeable and helpful. We booked the tour without the hotel package which was totally okay for everybody. Be aware that the local guides show you also some demonstrations of local crafts. It really depends on you if you want to buy something from the stores. Nobody is pressuring you into something. The whole tour is really worth the money if you want a seamless tour without to worry about guides and transportation.
reviews.title: A fantastic tour which is definitely worth the money

reviews.text: It was a great experience. Our driver Ashok was such a gentleman. Most of our local guide were very knowledgeable and the hotels were generally very well picked. I would definitely do it again.
reviews.title: 5 star experience!

ownerResponse.text:
We are glad to know that you liked your driver, Guides and hotels.

We hope to see you again in the future.

Best regards,
Team Golden Triangle Delhi Agra Jaipur Tour / Crystal India Holidays.

reviews.text:
We had an awesome trip and wonderful experience. The places we visited were amazing, the Hotels were top quality. 

The tour guides (Naresh, Maneesh and Mukesh) were polite, nice, knowledgeable and helpful. They would not only be tour guides but also take pictures, show best places/angles for photos, help us carrying stuff and provide advice. 

Our driver Bindar was excellent as well. He was nice, respectful, polite, helpful and gave us a peaceful, comfortable drive through the "colorful" traffic of India. Bindar would also accommodate to support small special requests outside the tour itinerary.

We didn't have face-to-face contact with the local tour operator (Amit), but he was very efficient in the previous coordination, communication, logistics, package preparation and instruction manual. He was also flexible in allowing us to make changes to the trip.

We are very happy with the tour. One advice to reduce your time in car would be to make separate flights arriving in Delhi but departing back from Jaipur (or vice versa).
reviews.title: Una maravilla!

reviews.text: Excellent way to see the major sites in India in 4 days. You have a personal driver ( Annu was amazing, kind, helpful and funny). We toured New Dehli with a tourguide who was very informative. Then we drove to Agra to the Taj Mahal. Our guide Racheed was amazing with the camera, knowing the ins and outs of each location. We arrived at the Taj Mahal at 5 am just so we could get amazing photos with no people in the background. Then onto the Tiger Safari. The Tigress hotel was gorgeous! The highest praise goes to our driver Sharwan Kumar, who’s great humour, knowledge and tentativeness, made the long daily drives fly by. reviews.text:
Our coordinator, Amit did a fantastic job with communication and trip logistics. Responded quickly to my messages and arranged for pickup at the hotel we were staying at (somewhat outside of downtown Delhi, as we were there for a wedding). Our driver, Sohan arrived early and was prompt and professional throughout the entire trip. Car was in excellent working order (especially A/C)! 

Licensed, local guides at each stop (Delhi, Agra, Ranthambore, and Jaipur) who were very knowledgeable and friendly. In particular, our guides in Agra (Manush) and Jaipur (Yogi) were outstanding (and took GREAT photographs)! Great dining recommendations by our guides and our driver.

We paid for the 5-star option on hotels. All three (Jaypee Palace in Agra, Tigress in Ranthambore, and Radisson in Jaipur) were outstanding. Staff at each went out of their way to make us feel welcome. Our server at the Tigress, Bhatti Lai was particularly memorable in the level of service he provided. 

If we were to do it over again, I wouldn't have done it any other way. Visiting the Golden Triangle is a singular experience - this is the way to do it.

Some cautions: drive times between cities are LONG (as in several hours); be ready. Also, we found that we needed quite a bit more cash then was recommended (though I'll admit that we tend to be generous tippers). I think we needed about INR30,000 in cash to cover admissions and tips for everyone (restaurants took Visa). We also discovered that we were limited to INR10,000 max on our withdrawals at ATMs (not sure if it was just our bank) so plan accordingly.
reviews.title: This the THE way to see the Golden Triangle

reviews.text:
I had a great time traveling through Delhi with our guide Shaily and our driver Surinder. I had a full day of sightseeing at the various stops included on the tour. Humaiyan's Tomb was probably my favorite stop on the tour - it was so large that it didn't feel crowded despite how many people were there. Some of the other stops were pretty dense with people, but they were all still enjoyable.

Driving on the streets was a little scary at first with how congested they are, but our driver drove very well and kept us safe during the trip.

Also, if you go in the winter, you're likely to experience fairly thick smog during the day - definitely bring an N95 mask. It can make some of the landmarks a little hazy, but you can't really avoid it.

Our guide was very knowledgeable, kind, and enjoyable to talk to. She was always nearby to help guide us through the sites (barring the one that doesn't allow private guides) and took a ton of great pictures for us along the way. She also kept us engaged in-between sites as we drove through traffic. Shaily and Surinder even went out of their ways to show us additional sites along the way, like a historic “haunted” well on our way to our lunch location, and a crowd of monkeys on the side of the road.

However, the tour company requires a mandatory shopping stop at a predatory store called “Delhi Haat Craft Cottage Industries” meant to trick foreigners who want to go to Dilli Haat, a government-run handicraft market. We couldn’t leave until we were shown each one of the store’s 4 floors full of overpriced items galore. Some salesmen let us go when we made it clear that we weren’t going to buy anything, but the painting guy in particular kept us for a long time trying to get me to buy “only one piece.” According to Google reviews, the “pashmina” scarves and “hand-woven” rugs are also fake, and they send you a fake bank statement after requesting a refund. My recommendation is to drink the chai as quickly as possible, refuse all of the products, then get out to your last stop. I don’t hold our guide responsible for this as it seems to be a mandate passed down from management, and she didn’t make any false pretenses about the stop, she just informed us that we would be able to see some interesting products should we wish to buy them.

Overall, I would still highly recommend this tour, but be prepared to resist the sell near the end.
reviews.title: Excellent tour through Delhi, but beware predatory shopping stop

First the driver was supposed to pick us up at 7am but ended up showing up at 9am due to incorrect information given to him by his company. When we when reached the Taj Mahal I thought everything would be fine but I was very wrong. 
	1.	The tour guide kept leaving us cutting through the lines which was very uncomfortable since people were waiting for a while. 
	2.	The tour guide didn’t know that a member of our group spoke Hindi and said to a photographer who was trying to sell us his services “ They are playing hard to get and don’t want to buy anything”. That’s not very respectful to say. 
	3.	He repeated the same information a thousand times and gave no substance to the tour. 
	4.	He tried to make us pay for the rickshaw to and from the Taj Mahal when it was the company’s responsibility. 
	5.	They couldn’t find the driver to take us back home. 
Overall, I’m very disappointed with this experience and hope that no one has to endure this kind of treatment.

Our tour guide Kaif and our driver Pradeep were super responsible, respectful, knowledgable, and caring about our tour and us.

Pradeep showed on time at our hotel in Delhi and drove us all the way to Agra. He was taking care of our needs and making sure he was there when we were out of every single site.

On another note, I recommend two things, first, try to be early because it gets super crowded and people don’t respect the queues :( we had a small incident because of that. Secondly, check how foggy it will be, it makes a huge difference.

Furthermore, just consider if it is worth hiring any photographer from the place (I don’t think so) because they charge you per picture and I made that mistake.

In the end, our day was enjoyable thanks to our tour guide and driver but make sure you plan it properly.

I believe a day of driving must be exhausting, but he still provided us with very satisfactory service. Thank you."

reviews.text:
In early November, we visited Doha and opted for this itinerary. The weather was pleasantly cool, and the historical landmarks were truly astounding. We learned a lot during this trip. The itinerary stated a full-day tour of 6-8 hours. We departed from the hotel at 11 a.m. and concluded our journey at 6 p.m. for the return trip, estimating we'd return to the hotel right on time after eight hours.

Unfortunately, sunset in Doha began as early as 4:30 p.m., so due to time constraints, we had to skip the camel track. Despite the guide's efforts to drive quickly, we arrived at the final attraction when it was already completely dark.

Despite these disappointments, we're immensely grateful to our guide, Noor Raja, who was incredibly patient, friendly, and knowledgeable. He provided commentary on the scenery and history throughout the trip, provided food for the children, and even offered us tea to refresh. I would rate this itinerary four stars due to a few minor disappointments, but the guide deserves five stars.
reviews.title: North and west trip in Doha

reviews.text: Asim drove us to the West & North of Qatar and in the way explained us the many things we didn't know about this country: history, culture, traditions,religion...For sure a complete and very interesting itinerary to make when visiting the country, way more fascinating than doing the dunes bashing! Many thanks Asim who took care of everything for us! Very recommended!
reviews.title: A complete Qatar experience

reviews.text: Fantastic tour! Sajid explained everything about Qatar and the discovery of some hidden gems of Qatar was just great!

reviews.text: We had an unforgetable tour with our great guide and driver Asim. We booked a Full Day Qatar's North and West Private Tour to be picked up at 8:00 a.m. in front of our amazing Najd Boutique hotel amidst Souk Waqif in the center of Doha. At 8:00 a.m. Asim waited for us in his very comfortable and well air-conditioned car and we could start our tour on time. Asim was a knowledgeable and competent guide who explained everything what was important to know about the sightseeing objects in a relatively compact form but he gave us also the time to relax when we wanted that. Asim spoke a very good English, was very helpful and was listening and responding on our wishes. We can Asim highly recommend to other customers, he is a wonderful person. We went into the direction of the west coast and our first stop was the camel race track, very interesting. Then we moved -in parts off-road - into the direction of Zekreet peninsula to the remarkable umbrella shaped rock and other exotic limestone formations, a favorite place for photography. We reached the remains of Zekreet Fort, a historical landmark there and the East/West-West/East art work by Richard Serra, four steel plates, each over fourteen meters in height. Situated on the north-western part of Qatar, we reached the Al-Zubarah Fort, the first UNESCO World Heritage site of Qatar and visited several other excavations nearby. Driving to the eastern coast line we asked Asim if it would be possible to see the Lusail football stadium in Katar's future city Lusail and the Katara Cultural Village at the edge of Doha. And it was really great that Asim modified the scheduled tour plan in an appropriate manner: We directly passed the nice city Al Khor and indeed he gave us the time to see (from outside) the football stadium surrounded by spctacular buildings and to do a 1-hour walk through the Cultural Village with the Opera House, the Amphitheater, the mosque and other interesting objects with finally, the beach area and a nice view on the skyline of Doha. He also changed the drop-off place from the hotel into the Villaggio mall, so that it was easy for us in the remaining time from 3:00 p.m. to have an own shopping experience, seeing another football stadium there and going back to the hotel via Metro (a technical innovation going driver-less) to visit still during day-light the phantastic National museum and the Museum for Islamic Art. Thank you Asim for this combined adventure tour.

reviews.text:
We took our teenage kids on the tour of the Sachsenhousen Concentration Camp one of the days we were in Germany. George was our tour guide, he had great knowledge and passion about what we were about to experience. 
The meet up location was easy to find, we had a few minutes to get some danishes for the road. There was a 45 min train ride to the camp/museum and it was a picturesque journey through towns and tree scapes.
On the short walk to the to the camp, George shared that the history (past and present)that the town shared with the camp. SS houses next to the camp are still lived in.
At the start of the camp and throughout the tour, George shared historical information that doesn’t always get emphasized. He did a great job giving reverence to the subject and being knowledgeable for questions asked. 
Although it was a 6 hour tour it went by really fast. I would highly recommend this tour, it was an incredible way to spend the day. I’m glad our kids got to see first hand the historical evidence of the individuals who had their lives altered through this camp.
reviews.title: Lessons of Life

This was an excellent and very memorable day trip. I was nervous what it’d be like - especially as I was taking my 15 and 18 year old sons. I needn’t have worried. Insider Tours were fantastic. Our big group was divided into 3 groups of around 25 people each. All 3 guides were excellent and went off independently so we weren’t waiting on all the others. 

We had a fantastic guide, Xavier, who was so knowledgable, kind, sensitive, wise and handled the whole trip and all the information superbly. He taught us all a great deal of interesting and useful things when we asked him questions on the train journeys - eg about relevant history and about Germany and Berlin today. My sons are not easy to impress, and thought they knew loads already from studying WW2 at school. But they were super-interested and engaged and focused throughout the whole day. 

Xavier (and the other guides who were on a similar timescale, I’m guessing) kept things moving at a good pace so we learnt and saw loads, but didn’t get too overwhelmed by the trip at any point. 

I’d thought about going just ourselves with no guide in case we got stuck on a long tour that we couldn’t leave. However, I see now that that would have been by far the worse option. I am so, so glad we saw Sachsenhausen on a good tour like Insider Tours. The momentum stayed good and we got so much more out of it with a quality guide. Also it is a big, complex place to see, with lots to learn, and I’d much rather have a skilled guide than need to listen to audio guides throughout and face the trip feeling alone with it all. Also it's a profoundly moving experience and I was glad we had the support of being with a kind and sympathetic guide.

reviews.text:
This is such an important experience. If you’re debating going to a concentration camp or not when visiting Berlin, you should. The history is difficult but cannot be avoided, especially given the times we currently live in. The museum is organized to tell the experience and history of the space, without it being traumatizing. Our group was concerned about what we may encounter in the tour, but there were ultimately no anxiety-inducing moments. 

Our guide, Hannah, was incredibly knowledgeable and intentional about how she handled the tour. Her personal touch made it even more effective. She is welcoming without judgment, and even ended the tour with her recommendations for Berlin. 

A few tips for the experience. It is largely outdoors, so plan accordingly for the weather. Also, eat a filling breakfast and bring a snack you can carry on you and water. Chocolate is a nice treat to have on the ride home. There are no meal options once you leave Berlin. You will experience the full walk that prisoners were put through, so prepare to be walking.
reviews.title: Impactful Experience

reviews.text:
Fantastic tour. There was a big group of people when we met at the starting point. Insider Tours had 3 guides available and we split into 3 groups of around 25. All guides seemed lovely. We had Xavier who was absolutely fantastic. He was very interesting and knowledgable - on the journey there he was funny and engaging and told us loads about German history before and after the war - answering all the questions from people in our group.

 Our group was pretty young. I’d been nervous about taking my 2 teenage sons - 15 & 18. I needn’t have worried. He kept them engaged and focused. 

When we got to the camp, Xavier gave brilliant information in a sensitive, thoughtful way. He took us around the whole camp at a really good pace so that we learnt loads but didn’t get too overwhelmed or lost momentum. I have lost family members in concentration camps and I felt Xavier was profoundly respectful and thoughtful in what he said. He didn’t know my family history when we were on the tour. 

The tour says 3 hours but that is the time spent in the camp. We left Berlin at 10am and returned around 4.15pm, with the train trip included. 

We took water and snacks, and ate our snacks after we left the camp. 

There are displays and small museum-type areas in parts of the camp. I’d wondered about just going ourselves, but I’m really glad we went with a quality guide. I think we got loads more out of the day and were able to see and understand a lot more in the time we had. 3 hours was a good amount of time to see and learn a lot but not get beyond the point that we could not take it in anymore.

reviews.text:
Each year, I take a solo trip for Christmas, and I try to fill them with all the things important to me on a holiday: sightseeing, learning, history, and fun. Neuschwanstein was naturally at the top of my list for this trip, and this tour did not disappoint. 

Charlie was my guide, and he was fantastic. Usually there are two guides per tour; but Charlie had to handle all of us on our own as the other was sick. Charlie is a great docent, for all the usual reasons: he's knowledgeable, friendly, etc. But he shines in two specific areas: taking the subject matter seriously and caring deeply about his guests. The level of care displayed was phenomenal, and it truly felt like Charlie already somehow knew each of us. And in terms of his style, he avoids the usual corny jokes one usually hears on tours. He doesn't treat the subject matter as boring, using jokes to fill in where insecurity reigns. Instead, he treats the subject matter with respect, and encourages the group to do the same. It was really cool!

Also traveling solo? Here's an easy tip: board the bus first ;-)
reviews.title: Awesome Tour

reviews.text:
This is a tough one to review, so the highs and lows are below. 

Positives: 
- Charlie was a great guide and even though he talked a little too much, he clearly knew his stuff and was very friendly. 
- The castle itself is well worth a visit! 

Negatives: 
- The timing of the day! There was SO much waiting around in the cold. We had an hour for lunch and to explore the village, but then 1.5 hours to walk/ bus/ carriage up to the castle which takes at most 40 mins if you walk. Then there was another 1.5 hours to get back down to the meeting point (again, max 40 minutes). It’s cold up there in winter and there’s no shelter from the rain so they seriously need to adjust their timings. 
- The cost: you pay extra for the castle, extra for lunch, extra for the carriage or bus ride. I’m still not sure where the €60 goes. 
- We booked expecting a max of 25 people in our group so were disappointed when we ended up with 52. 

Castle: 5/5
Charlie: 4/5 
Overall tour: 2/5 

If you can get up there yourself, it’s a much better choice than taking a tour.
reviews.title: Skip the tour, hire a car instead

ownerResponse.text:
Hi Isabelle. 
Sorry to read that you were left overall underwhelmed by the tour experience. Let me try and address some of your points. 

I believe it was a somewhat rainy day when you traveled and Charlie will have talked a little more than usual on the bus to avoid the group being unnecessarily stood out in the rain listening to him talk more. This will have likely also been communicated to the group. On less rainy days the information could be more evenly distributed throughout the day and perhaps not come across as too much. 

The timings are set the way they are to allow enough time for people to make their way up to the castle whichever way they choose by either bus, carriage or walking, even on busier days with potential queues for transport. There are a number of view points to be enjoyed during this time also and most guests are happy to have the extra time to soak in the beautiful surroundings.

Some of the 1.5h you mentioned to walk down could have been spent exploring more of the inside of the castle. Our guides usually explain this is more free time after the guided castle tour and can be used as people wish. The walk down is only around 30mins so people are typically advised to either spend more time in the castle or walk down earlier to grab food in the village. 

The optional castle entry ticket is clearly advertised as an additional cost as are the bus and carriage ride up the the castle. Lunch is not advertised as included in the tour, though time is allocated for those who wish to purchase something. 
The tour was supposed to have been led by two guides who would have split the group into two groups of 26 (total 52) One of our guides we found out was ill on the day so rather than cancel the tour for 26 people the tour ran with one guide. this was a last minute decision we felt resulted in more overall customer satisfaction. Given the multiple 5star reviews from other guests joining the tour that day that seems to have been the case. 

We also agree those who are less interested in learning from our guides and who don't mind pre booking tickets well in advance and figuring out the logistics of getting there and up to the castle on time are probably better off doing it themselves. For those who prefer turning up and having everything taken care of who also enjoy learning from our guides a guided tour provides just those benefits. 

Regards
Radius Tours

This is well worth it as a day trip from Munich, although it is a full on day! Our guides, Charlie and Michelle, were absolutely brilliant and made sure we didn’t get bored on the journey there with lots of fantastic background information that helped us to really appreciate the castle when we got there. 

Be aware that the bus up the hill doesn’t run in the winter, so it is a substantial hike! Wear sensible shoes and bring plenty of water - it isn’t the easiest trek! There is a horse and carriage which can take you most of the way up the hill but I saw it didn’t run the full way, so definitely one to consider if you have mobility issues - you will need to trek uphill a bit! Michelle was brilliant at taking us up the hill in stages and at each pause giving us more information on Ludvig II which helped to keep the walk interesting.

reviews.text:
2 part review…

First, the logistics were absolutely horrendous and their process needs to be changed. About 2 hours into the bus ride, we stopped at a rest stop/McDonalds. As we were walking out of the rest stop towards the bus, the bus pulled away and left without us. No one answered the “emergency” number provided by the tour operator. We were fortunate that another bus pulled up shortly after and we arranged to go with that tour group to Berlin instead. While on our second bus, a women mentioned that she wasn’t even part of this tour, but got on the bus thinking the bus would take her to the train  station where she had another tour waiting. There were no names being checked off when starting the tour and apparently no headcount being taken being taken at stops. Be warned!!

Now for the actual tour - Johnny our guide was outstanding! He turned the day around for us. He was tremendously knowledgeable, funny, and made the experience worthwhile. We never felt rushed and had adequate time to see what was on the itinerary. The history and stories told about Berlin and its people were incredible.
reviews.title: Actual tour was excellent!

ownerResponse.text:
Dear Paul,

Thank you for sharing your feedback regarding your recent tour experience.

Our operator was occupied with another call when your call came through. However, we did receive and promptly respond to the message you sent us, immediately contacting the other bus driver to ensure you were picked up. We realize that this must have been a situation that caused some anxiety, however we feel it is worth mentioning that we resolved the issue within a matter of minutes and ensured that you arrived in Berlin safe and sound and were able to join a great tour.

Regarding the passenger check-in process, we do in fact have passenger lists and check-ins. It is worth noting that the day of your tour was one of the busiest ones of the season, during which we organized 9 buses and over 300 passengers. Furthermore, the ship was 30 minutes delayed in docking, which meant that when it finally docked, thousands of passengers spilled out quickly. Despite this, our port assistants managed to efficiently organize over 300 passengers onto 9 buses within 15 minutes - not an easy feat, and one only possible precisely because of our organization. This rapid action enabled us to give everyone who booked with us to get o Berlin with enough time to give everyone a great tour even with the delay from the ship. Nevertheless, we acknowledge that in such a high-pressure situation, some oversight can occur, and we deeply regret that you experienced the consequences of this.

On a positive note, we are thrilled to hear that Johnny, your guide, made a significant impact on your tour experience. Johnny is indeed one of our most knowledgeable and engaging guides in Berlin. We appreciate your kind words about his expertise, humor, and ability to create a memorable experience. We will pass along your compliments to Johnny, as recognition of his outstanding work.

Once again, we apologize for the inconveniences you faced during the logistics process, and we truly appreciate your understanding of the challenges we encountered that day. We value your feedback, as it helps us identify areas for improvement. We hope to have the opportunity to serve you again in the future and provide you with an exceptional tour experience from start to finish.

If you have any further concerns or questions, please don't hesitate to reach out to our customer service team. Thank you for choosing our tour service.

reviews.text: Felt like we were in good hands throughout the trip - starting from our event organiser, Amit, was understanding and the most helpful throughout our journey. Our personal driver, Mr Singh, was also prompt and helpful - utterly grateful for his services. All three guides in all three cities were knowledgeable, kind, friendly and helpful. They knew the ins and outs of each city well and knew which areas were requiring to be more cautious in. If we were to return to India, we would definitely return to the same event organiser and hope there are other places they can provide tour guides in!

reviews.text:
This tour was the perfect introduction to north India. We were met from our flight by Annu our driver and spent the day seeing the sights and sounds of Delhi with a tour guide. Annu stayed with the car and dropped us at places and picked us up after. We then moved on to Agra for an overnight stay in a fabulous hotel. A different guide on day 2 was excellent and knew where to take all the best photos! Then it was on to Jaipur, which is just beautiful. Again, a new tour guide but all 3 were excellent. 
Annu is an excellent driver and his car was always spotless. He was great company on the longer parts of the drive too. 
Really recommend this tour, although my only regret is that we didn’t stay for 2 nights in Jaipur. There was just so much to see and so little time!

reviews.text: We had a fantastic trip with Crystal India Holidays to see the Golden Triangle! There were so many logistics involved with our visit (I’m sure many of them we never even knew about), and they were handled flawlessly. Our driver was incredible, and we had three excellent and knowledgeable guides each day. The hotels were excellent as well. Looking back, it would have been impossible for us to coordinate a trip like this on our own, especially as first-time visitors to India. I highly recommend Crystal India Holidays for anyone hoping to see the Golden Triangle. Thank you!
reviews.title: Wonderful experience at the Golden Triangle!

reviews.text: I was a solo traveller and the travel safety aspect was very important to me. The driver assigned to my trip (Dharmender) was friendly and courteous and drove safely and carefully on busy, chaotic roads. All the tour guides had good knowledge of the historic monuments I visited and I learnt a lot from them.  I felt protected and safe in their presence. The lunch eating places suggested by Viator were adequate and the 5 star hotels I opted for were of high standards with buffet dinner and breakfast included. The visits to factory shops offered an insight to the skills of the local artisans and an array of products to purchase. I highly recommend this tour as a great way of seeing the amazing wonders of India.
reviews.title: Excellent and authentic travel experience

reviews.text: A really excellent tour. First time in India, all arrangements worked smoothly: good car (excellent condition, plenty of legroom and headroom); excellent driver (careful, respectful, helpful); two excellent 5-star hotels, in Agra and Jaipur; three good guides (one really excellent). To be honest I don't know how the company/agency does it: to organise everything yet, given the expenses, still make a worthwhile profit. Anyway, trying to arrange similar would have required a lot of work, cost far more. Highly recommended, wouldn't hesitate for one moment to book with them (Crystal India Holidays) again.

reviews.text:
Yesterday was just about perfect.  Our guide, Melanie, was there waiting for us under the canopy.  At the stroke of 3PM we headed into the Rathskeller for the first food stop – which was an individual plate with small samples of several German favorites, pretzel & mustard, 2 meats, cooked red cabbage, plus spätzle.  Then a leisurely walk through Lockerbie Square, where the guide had arranged an abbreviated (first floor only) visit to the James Whitcomb Riley house – really fun to see the original 1800’s kitchen.  

Then a brief walk to the Lockerbie Pub for a scaled-down version of their famous Hoosier tenderloin with all the trimmings (including breaded, deep-fried pickle discs) plus flights of 3 different craft beers or wine samples.  An extra surprise was that Mayor Joe Hogsett had finished his lunch there and said hello to us on his way out.

Next stop was Rooster’s Kitchen on Mass Ave. – near the Bottle Works construction - never heard of this spot.  Our reserved table was ready and the 8 of use were treated to a smaller version of their popular brisket sandwich on buttered & toasted sourdough bread, with a side dish of “charred carrots” – small strips of carrots brushed in olive oil and seared on the grill.  

By now we were stuffed but enjoyed a final stop on Mass Ave. at The Best Chocolate in Town for various chocolate treats or choice of ice cream flavors.   

Three of the seven were from Chicago, four of us from Indy.  We all got along well especially after the flights of beer.  Melanie is a local nurse and does this as a second job – and her many stories about the area were interesting.  By the time we were done almost 3 hours had passed – with a fun group and great weather.  Could not have been better!
reviews.title: Truly a delightful experience.

Dear Gary, 

Thank you for taking the time to share your experience with us regarding the Venice In a Day tour. 

We regret hearing about the challenges you faced in contacting us and joining the tour promptly. 

It is disappointing that you missed the first half of the experience and felt uncomfortable with our guide's demeanor. 

Please accept our apologies for any frustration caused.

We encourage you to contact us at feedback@walks.org so we can further investigate the issue and understand how we can improve our services. 

Additionally, we would like to remind you that our telephone number is in your tour voucher. 

While we strive to assist through text messages, calling might offer a quicker resolution in time-sensitive situations.

We understand that finding the meeting point can be challenging, and we genuinely aim to help our clients navigate these situations. However, we also want to clarify that in cases where clients are late and miss part of the tour, it is beyond our control. 

Nonetheless, we are committed to being as accommodating as possible and appreciate your understanding in such matters.

Thank you for choosing our tour, and we look forward to hearing from you to address any further concerns you may have.

Best regards,

Jhonas.
Walks and Devour Tours.

reviews.text:
We dove with Pure Dive Resort during the end of our trip to Bali at the beginning of June.  We got the stay and dive package so we stayed for 3 days at the Sameton Hotel and dove for 2 days with Pure Dive.  The staff communicated with us very well and we were able to make sure we had exactly what we wanted for our stay and dive.  From arranging our ferries to our transport to the hotel, everything was excellent.

We were happy to find a great dive center that accommodated all levels of divers.  The dive masters were friendly and helpful, so were the crew of the boat.   We felt very safe the whole time and were able to fully enjoy our diving experience.  The gear was well maintained and everything went smoothy, from the dive plan briefing, all the way to the review of the dives at lunch time.

We did 2 dives per day and had an amazing time.  We went to Manta Point and were lucky enough to see several huge Manta.  We also did dives at Suana, Toyapakeh Wall, and SD Point.  The coral life around Nusa Penida was amazing.   We could have done more dives per day, but we know how exhausting that can be so we just stuck with 2.   

The accommodations at the Sameton hotel were conveniently located just down the street from Pure Dive.   We had a lot of good food from the local warungs, and there were some beach clubs there too if you like that sort of thing.

There was one incident where another diver accidentally took my mask instead of their own when we returned to shore.   I communicated with the owner and she and the staff tried to locate my missing mask even so far as contacting all of the other guests.  Unfortunately it could not be found.  But she offered to pay for my missing mask which was very kind and professional.

We would definitely dive again with Pure Dive Resort.   They made our final days in Bali very memorable and it felt like we were staying with family.  So please visit with Pure Dive Resort, where tomorrow is always Manta Trip.
reviews.title: Tomorrow is always Manta Trip

reviews.text: Starting at pickup winding through the villages of Bali seeing all the locals walking to the water purification temple. Getting to the Luwak coffee plantation and then onto top the mountain. All an adventure in itself, then to continue onto the downhill cycle. We chose our bike and helmet and checked everything over. The guide then explained the gears and brakes, and a few pointers to us before starting. It was so amazing, the fields of mandarin’s, chilies, and marigolds. We meandered through it all asking questions and shouting back to the others so they heard also. We saw a family compound, a temple, a school, the president’s grounds, and so much more. The tour guide had fantastic English and was able to answer all the common and obscure questions on culture, history, and politics, posed to him by all of us on the tour. We truly learned and discovered so much from the experience that, I now have such a huge appreciation of Bali and its people. Followed by an amazing lunch from the kitchen staff and cold drinks. I felt well thought of and catered for, even having a refreshing towel after the 30km was unexpected and very appreciated. This is a tour for any fitness level as its all downhill, through the back roads and villages of beautiful Bali. Highly recommend for anyone wanting a genuine day out in Bali to experience a huge variety of the elements of Balinese lifestyle.

reviews.text:
Food Variety

At Anggrek Putih cooking class in Lombok, each participant prepares one dish, meaning the larger your group, the greater the variety to try. Participants in our group could choose their cooking station (and thereby which dish they wanted to prepare) on a first come first served basis. We had 10 people in our group and were able to prepare/taste: Beef Stew (Beef Rendang), Chicken Satay (Sate Ayam), Corn Fritters (Perkedel Jagung), Fried Noodles (Mie Goreng), Fried Rice (Nasi Goreng), Grilled Fish in Banana Leaf (Pepes Ikan), Vegetables in Peanut Sauce (Gado Gado), Chicken Soup (Soto Ayam), Sweet and Sour Shrimp (Udang Asam Manis) and Fried Eggplant (Terung Goreng).

Food Quality

The food quality is outstanding. Many of the ingredients come straight from the on-site organic garden. Before the cooking class starts, participants are given a tour of the garden and can taste veggies fresh off the plants.

Instructions

Our group had two instructors, one for every 5 participants, who would first show us (individually) what to do and then we would do it ourselves. Now and then, they would check on our progress and provide tips. Recipes are shared after the class (as PDF documents) – so there is no need to take any notes.

Venue

Tiled and impeccably clean, the large covered open-air kitchen is set in a lush garden (together with other buildings, including a guesthouse and pool). Overhead fans provide a pleasant breeze in the hot afternoon. The L-shaped table layout with individual cooking stations for each person was a great set-up as it allowed me to observe and interact with other participants. There is a spacious dining table where all participants gather to enjoy the delicious dishes they prepare. Last but not least, a clean unisex toilet in easy reach from the kitchen completes the facilities.

Staff

Anggrek Putih is a family-run affair. Chris, the Greek owner who has lived in Indonesia since 2005, led our tour around the garden and made sure our glasses were always filled. His Indonesian wife, Dewi, and another Indonesian lady provided the instructions during our class (and I’m sure did a lot of other things behind the scenes). All speak English well and are very personable. Even though the cooking class has been provided for years, the team genuinely cares, and the experience felt very personal. Nothing transactional about it (unlike some other activities in Indonesia).

Sustainability

At Anggrek Putih, sustainability is a priority. Ingredients are sourced primarily from the on-site organic garden. No food is wasted: cut-offs are composted and participants receive any leftovers to take “home”. To further improve, we recommend Anggrek Putih consider wrapping leftovers in banana leaves (where appropriate) or using other bio-degradable packaging instead of (single-use) plastic containers.

CONCLUSION

The Anggrek Putih cooking class and garden tour in Lombok is a great, fun afternoon activity – whether you’re a single traveller, a couple or a family (and whatever cooking experience you have). Chris and his team have perfected their cooking class experience over the years, and there is not much the team can improve upon. Our only (other) suggestion would be to keep the photo session shorter: After the welcome drink, garden tour and welcome snack, we were just keen to get started cooking.
reviews.title: After a unique cooking class in Lombok? Head to Anggrek Putih

Hi James, thanks for your feedback in this review. As a small surf company in Santa Barbara we strive to provide 5 star experiences everytime we provide a surf lesson. We're so glad to hear that our office team accommodated your custom request. We're also pumped to hear that our instructors were so professional and helpful. 

As we mentioned over the phone, where we hosted your surf lesson was not the beach location we recommended but a beach that you requested we host your lesson at despite us recommending against it. 

With the accommodation of the custom beach location on a busy Saturday in July we were only able to offer 2 instructors. We also typically assign 1 instructor per 5 surfers and when the 11th surfer was added the day prior we were already sold out on instructors for that day.

I hope this helps bring clarity to why your lesson felt more like a 4 star experience instead of a 5 star experience. 

Lastly, thank you so much for your kind words and for booking a surf lesson with us. We are so stoked that it was a good day for the family during your stay at the Ritz Carlton.

reviews.text:
Lok Virsa Museum: This museum showcases the cultural heritage of Pakistan, featuring traditional crafts, music, art, and historical artifacts.

Pakistan Monument: The Pakistan Monument is a national symbol representing the four provinces and three territories of Pakistan. It's a striking structure and a great spot for photography.

Daman-e-Koh: Situated in the Margalla Hills, Daman-e-Koh offers a panoramic view of Islamabad. It's a popular spot for picnics and nature enthusiasts.

Rawal Lake: An artificial reservoir in Islamabad, Rawal Lake is a serene place for boating and picnicking. The picturesque surroundings make it a favorite spot for both locals and tourists.

Pakistan Museum of Natural History: This museum showcases the diverse flora and fauna of Pakistan, making it an educational and interesting visit, especially for nature lovers.

Shakarparian Park: Located near Zero Point, Shakarparian Park offers a beautiful view of Islamabad and is an ideal spot for evening walks and family outings.

Rose and Jasmine Garden: These gardens are known for their stunning floral displays. The Rose Garden, in particular, is a colorful spectacle during the blooming season.

Taxila Museum: While not in Islamabad itself, Taxila, located nearby, is an ancient archaeological site with a museum that houses artifacts from the Gandhara civilization, providing a glimpse into Pakistan's ancient history.

When planning your visit, it's a good idea to check the local guidelines and any travel advisories, especially considering the dynamic nature of travel conditions. Enjoy your visit to these historical and cultural sites in Islamabad!
reviews.title: Faisal Masjid Islamabad

reviews.text:
Ronaldo and L from Galicia, Spain
   We had a beautiful day in July ina Islamabad with our guide Maqsood and his driver that took us around the city.
   This small tour, about eight hours, around the beautiful town of Islamabad is a really good introduction to the capital of Pakistan and gives you a good welcoming picture of the city and the life there. It's a balanced tour between the country up in the mountains and the city.
   What surprised us was that Islamabad is so green, trees in all streets, and parks everywhere and it makes it really an oasis in a dry world. From Daman-e-Koh we could see the whole city and the dominant colour is of course the green. The mosque Faisal is also placed in a beautiful setting surrounded by the mountains.
   So it was a memorable day, of course we asked our guide Maqsood to put his favourite pakistan music while travelling in the car, and so we had the opportunity to enjoy among others the fantastic Ustad Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan  singing the unforgettable Aankh Uthi Mohabbat Ne Angrai Li.
reviews.title: Excellent introduction to a beautiful capital

reviews.text: Jan is an incredibly knowledgeable and charismatic tour guide, with a clear passion for Vienna's eclectic history which he's able to make so contagious through vibrant story telling and interesting, often hilarious, facts, that we were actually interrupted mid tour by a documentary team asking if they could record his speech about one of the monuments he was explaining. Being very professional, he initially declined to break from his tour but I insisted he give a brief interview so that viewers of the documentary could enjoy his engaging speaking style and expertise too. His tour was really nuanced and tailored to the individual, offering an array of recommendations on where best to eat in the city and hidden gems, from the special backstreet cafe that serves coffee in cones through a window, to funny 'treasure hunts' for certain secrets of St Stephen's cathedral. He even provided a break in the tour to sample some culinary delights at one of the locals' preferred haunts for strudel and cake. The most special part of the tour for my family was the fact that we visited Vienna to celebrate the birthday of my late father, who was always intrigued by the history of the city; with this in mind, Jan kindly included facts he thought my dad would have liked to know after learning about him, and even made a beautiful suggestion of sponsoring a rose in memory of him at the Volkesgarten, a possibility I would never have known about without Jan's insight. I hope to visit again sometime and feel like I've left Vienna with a much deeper appreciation for the city, and with a new friend too.
reviews.title: The best tour of Vienna's past, featuring hidden gems and strudel!

Today me and my kids had a lifetime experience! This, we will never forget. A paraglide in Lienz with Daniel Kofler and his fellow pilots, René and Sigi. The team is very keen on safety so it felt all very good to go up the mountain with them and fly up to 500 meters above the ground. 

We ‘booked’ online and all info was given via whatsapp. The way Daniel communicates is great and makes you enthousiastic even before you are up in the air. 

If you go to Lienz, you have to get a flight for sure. You will not regret this!
reviews.title: A super paragliding experience in Lienz

reviews.text: It was amazing….thanks a lot! Best experience ever! Will do it again, for sure! Very nice flight instructors!
reviews.title: Astonishing

reviews.text: It was a fabulous flight over the valley en the mountains. We had more than 30 minutes of airtime. The instructors were really friendly, and helpful. Absolutely a most to do when your on vacation in this area.

reviews.text: Von Anfang an machte Daniel den Tandemflug zu einem unvergesslichen Erlebnis. Seine ruhige und kompetente Art gab mir sofort ein Gefühl von Sicherheit. Das Highlight unseres Fluges war mit Sicherheit, gemeinsam mit 2 Adlern die Thermik zu teilen. Die Adler schenkten uns zusätzlich eine spontane Acro-Show. Dieser Flug mit Daniel war nicht nur ein unvergessliches Erlebnis, sondern auch eine einzigartige Chance, die Natur aus einer neuen Perspektive zu erleben. Ich kann einen Tandemflug mit Daniel als Piloten im Airpark Lienz von ganzem Herzen empfehlen!
reviews.title: unvergesslich!

We had a great day with Wine Pro Tours up in Napa! Jeremy took us to some very unique and boutique wineries that were so welcoming! We would not have had this experience anywhere else to be sure. The Mercedes sprinter he picked us up in was very clean and comfortable. He also supplied us with endless waters which was vital on a day long adventure of wine tasting. Jeremy was not just our driver but also a tour guide and historian for each vineyard. He had incredible wine tasting tips and we were very appreciative of how seamless the transfer to each winery was. 

Highlights were: Unique wineries not open to the public, customer service, the wine!

Only thing we would change next time is budgeting for a little more wine as we were in love with all the wines but many were above $80/ bottle which begins to add up! In the future we may pick a more budget friendly selection of wineries as well but for a birthday it was definitely a luxurious experience!

If you want to experience an absolutely amazing day you must book with Jeremy from Wine tour pros.

Jeremy created a customized itinerary based on our requests.   We started the day taking photos of the Golden Gate bridge but not from where all the other tourist do it from the other side of the bridge in a private area that no one seem to know about. 

Next off to the Simoncini Winery where we enjoyed a private tour and five course lunch with wine pairings.   Did you hear me say private? We were the only five guests at this very exclusive winery.

 I’ve been to both Napa and Sonoma, however I’ve never experienced anything as fabulous like this before. 

We completed our day in the Armstrong redwood park relaxing on the trails and taking in the amazing views.

Jeremy is very professional, knowledgeable and friendly! 

 And also did I mention that this was a bucket list trip for my 84-year-old mother? She was over the moon!

Jeremy-  Can’t wait till we can come back and plan another trip. Thank you so much!

reviews.text: We did a tour of the Braastad distillery in Jarnac France. It was an hour and half with a personal guide called Eric. This is a family run distillery and the processes from grape to table are all done here. So you get to see how the grapes are distilled stored and bottled all in the one place and people are involved in working at each part of the process. The distillery is amazing and the cask storage is worth seeing. There is even cognac stored since 1845. They have bottles going back since the distillery first started. The history is so interesting and the process fascinating.  Our guide Eric was brilliant so informative and friendly he was happy to answer all our questions and made the place come alive for us. The tasting g at the end is great. You get to try the cognac and compare the different flavours. I would highly recommend this tour as an enjoyable interesting experience well with the time for a visit on your holiday.
reviews.title: Excellent tour very interesting well worth a visit.

Once on board the helicopter, put on the headsets to a very friendly pilot and we instantly knew we were in safe hands, the flight was circa 26 minutes and covered everything you would want to see in NYC which an excellent commentary and history lesson.  Both landing and take off were very smooth and has restored my confidence in flying again.  Don’t pick the cheapest online, pick the best a modern fleet of really comfortable (I am 6’4” and a big guy) but had no trouble getting in and out of the helicopter.

reviews.text:
We really enjoyed our husky experience. The transfer pick was on time and comfortable.  The suits and boots provided were super warm and excellent - it was very organised change room that was warm with helpful staff getting everyone correctly fitted out.  The staff were friendly and clearly loved and cared for the dogs.

We were told how to correctly approach and pat the huskies and sit on the sled.  

The husky ride to the tipi was fun - you are sitting almost snow level and going past the most incredible winter wonderland.  We went on morning tour, and in early Jan we had beautiful colours in the sky as we rode through.  A short fika break with lovely chat in the tipi and warm drinks and cinnamon buns before heading off on the return trip. We were able to visit and pat the husky puppies when we got back which was lovely.  There was plenty of opportunities for photos and husky pats.

The only downside to our experience was due to our height.  We are both tall, my husband is 6' 5". As the tallest, he was seated at the back of the sled to correctly balance it, with me in front and another 2 people in front of us.  As we had to ensure our feet were correctly on the sled (so as not to hit toes etc as you travel along), we really had to sit quite uncomfortably on the sled.  My feet had to be on top of his because I couldn't put them further forward due to a metal bar.  The positioning meant our knees and legs were quite uncomfortable and despite very much enjoying the experience, we were very keen to get ourselves off the sled.  I think if you are tall, it would be better to have more space on the sled if possible.  Not sure if a more private sled for 2 people would have resulted in a more comfortable ride.  However, I want to emphasise that we are both very glad to have experienced the husky ride and enjoyed the experience, huskies, staff, fika etc and would recommend Husky Tours Lapland.  The trails are quiet and peaceful with no one else around.
reviews.title: Winter wonderland ride

reviews.text: It was a unique and incredible experience! We were received punctually and with great attention. When we got there, they borrowed us proper winter clothes which was very important as it was a -30 degree C day. They allowed, encouraged and explained how to play with the dogs and that was really cool. The landscapes on the tour are beautiful and the sled is very safe! The Fika at the stop on the way was very pleasant, I felt like I was in ancient times. I regretted not taking my ski goggles because it was an extremely cold day. I would encourage using voice command to record images because taking off the glove is not a good idea. I highly recommend this tour.

Dana, our guide, and Arliss, our driver, were fantastic! Dana was enthusiastic and knowledgeable about the city. She was great about making sure we stayed on schedule so we made the ferry and didn't miss our chance to see anything or that the tour ran long. Her love and enthusiasm for NYC shone through the entire tour.

Arliss navigated through traffic and around obstacles and street closures without a hitch. The president was helo-ing into NYC that day and we ran into some closures around the Statton Island Ferry and other locations, but Dana and Arliss clearly knew they way around because, with only a minor adjustment to the schedule, the tour continued uninterrupted. Anytime we left the bus, Arliss was right there to pick us up afterwards. Both Dana and Arliss  were friendly and charming. We had a blast.

I highly recommend the small van tour since with 12 people you get a much more interactive experience and it is easier to hear and speak with the guide.

The tour and guide (Jim) were great.
Unfortunately I left my rucksack and possessions on the tour mini-bus which I later found went mysteriously missing. 
I reported the missing bag the same day, recalled the head office the next morning and re-visited the start point, tour van and staff in person the very next day before the first (10am) tour and searched the same van for my stuff.
I was informed by the staff on the street that the bag had not been located but was told by staff that after our tour (6hr tour) it was the last one of the day and the minibus went back to the yard. When I left the minibus and took selfie with the guide I saw all the other 9x ‘tourists’ had left the minibus. 
I have lost my $200 backpack and $500 rayban - thank god not my passport. After such a great tour disappointing that staff trust seems to be an issue with the company. Otherwise would have been 5star. Enjoy the rayban guys!
reviews.title: Great tour - don’t leave your stuff!

reviews.text:
In summary, a marvellous experience !  Four of us on a sledge, pulled by ten exuberant and very friendly Alaskan Huskies, under the command of Gaynor, our expert driver and guide.  
To experience a form of transport centuries old, gliding through frozen forest is quite something…Half through the trip we had a welcome break for coffee and apple cake round a fire … then the second half across a frozen river and lake. 
What was most obvious is the affection between the drivers and their dogs, the enjoyment the guides have in ‘doing their job’ and the care this small company take over their customers. As part of the price, they provide hi spec jackets, ski pants, mittens and boots and today, given the wind chill at -20, these were very welcome.
Lastly, thanks to Natalie, who drove us to and from the trail - a sledge driver too in her own right. A young woman from Bavaria, she ‘ came to Kiruna for a year, and this is my sixth !’ Obviously she loves her job, as you will love this trip.
reviews.title: Marvellous experience

ownerResponse.text: Hi and thank you so much for leaving such a great review. It was a pleasure to have you on my sled and I'm glad you could appreciate the beauty of it all as much as we do. Gaynor.

Joined this tour with my family on 12 Jan 2024 and our guide was Natalie. Natalie is very passionate about her job and she made sure everyone is well taken care of. 

Overall, we enjoyed the trip thoroughly. Got to see the beautiful winter scenery as we took the sled over frozen lake, led by the very friendly and hardworking huskies. We also had coffee and pastry in a tent with camp fire.

Was initially apprehensive about taking dog sled rides but it turns out that the guides are bigger animal lovers than me. They made sure the dogs are well-fed, well-rested and enjoy what they are doing.
